<i>Team Mentor Mile chose</i>

14
00:01:00,080 --> 00:01:02,280
<i>Peem, an intense young musician.</i>

15
00:01:02,800 --> 00:01:05,760
<i>Gluf, a smart and dapper young man.</i>

16
00:01:05,840 --> 00:01:09,360
<i>Manyoo, a pageant-ready national athlete.</i>

17
00:01:09,440 --> 00:01:12,160
<i>Leo, a highly talented Korean </i>Oppa<i>.</i>

18
00:01:12,680 --> 00:01:15,720
<i>And Jacob, biracial with a sweet face.</i>

19
00:01:15,800 --> 00:01:18,520
<i>As for Mentor Off, he chose</i>

20
00:01:18,600 --> 00:01:21,520
<i>Fox, a charming Thai-Australian.</i>

21
00:01:22,120 --> 00:01:24,800
<i>Rome, a professional model.</i>

22
00:01:24,880 --> 00:01:27,600
<i>Mew, a good-humored rapper.</i>

23
00:01:27,680 --> 00:01:30,560
<i>Pom, a gold-medalist athlete and model.</i>

24
00:01:30,640 --> 00:01:34,080
<i>Bonus, intense, tan, and fit.</i>

25
00:01:34,160 --> 00:01:40,040
<i>Which mentor will lead their team through</i>
<i>the campaigns to become the next Face?</i>

26
00:01:40,120 --> 00:01:41,800
<i>Let's find out.</i>

27
00:02:12,080 --> 00:02:14,840
<i>The winner</i>
<i>of </i>The Face Men Thailand Season 4

28
00:02:14,920 --> 00:02:17,400
<i>will collaborate with Clear Thailand.</i>

29
00:02:17,480 --> 00:02:19,320
<i>He will receive a one-year supply</i>

30
00:02:19,400 --> 00:02:22,920
<i>of Clear Ice Cool Menthol</i>
<i>and Clear Men Cool Sport Menthol.</i>

31
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:25,520
<i>And get the chance to work</i>
<i>with Vaseline Thailand.</i>

32
00:02:25,600 --> 00:02:29,920
<i>Plus, he'll receive</i>
<i>Vaseline SPF50+ PA++++,</i>

33
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:32,680
<i>Gluta Hyaluronic Acid,</i>
<i>Photoage Defense UV Serum</i>

34
00:02:32,760 --> 00:02:34,360
<i>free for an entire year.</i>

35
00:02:34,440 --> 00:02:36,080
<i>He will also collaborate with AXE.</i>

36
00:02:36,160 --> 00:02:39,560
<i>And receive a year's supply</i>
<i>of personal care products.</i>

37
00:02:39,640 --> 00:02:42,760
<i>Bearbeary, only the wearers feel it.</i>

38
00:02:42,840 --> 00:02:46,480
<i>Premium wear for every style,</i>
<i>featuring top design and innovation.</i>

39
00:02:46,560 --> 00:02:49,440
<i>They'll award a 100,000-baht gift voucher.</i>

40
00:02:49,520 --> 00:02:53,360
<i>Strive for perfection</i>
<i>with a membership to Hotman Fitness.</i>

41
00:02:53,440 --> 00:02:56,240
<i>Including an 18-month</i>
<i>personal training program.</i>

42
00:02:56,320 --> 00:02:59,920
<i>Plus a 200,000-baht package</i>
<i>from V Design Clinic.</i>

43
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:02,320
<i>Get ready to step onto the national screen</i>

44
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:05,360
<i>through a collaboration</i>
<i>with Channel 3 HD, Thailand.</i>

45
00:03:05,440 --> 00:03:09,920
<i>And sign an acting contract</i>
<i>with Kantana Group Public Company Limited,</i>

46
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:12,720
<i>Thailand's leading producer</i>
<i>of dramas and films.</i>

47
00:03:44,600 --> 00:03:48,560
Welcome to <i>The Face Men Thailand Season 4</i>.

48
00:03:48,640 --> 00:03:53,440
You're all part of <i>The Face </i>family now.

49
00:03:53,520 --> 00:03:56,920
From now on,
you'll carry The Face last name,

50
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:59,360
just like the contestants
from the past nine seasons

51
00:03:59,440 --> 00:04:02,400
who've made their mark
in the entertainment industry.

52
00:04:02,480 --> 00:04:06,040
Additionally, you'll be living
in a space fully furnished

53
00:04:06,120 --> 00:04:08,840
by Boonthavorn LIFESTYLE furniture.

54
00:04:08,920 --> 00:04:12,880
They make the whole place feel warm,
highly functional,

55
00:04:12,960 --> 00:04:15,160
and as comfortable as your own home.

56
00:04:15,240 --> 00:04:17,640
So, congratulations again.

57
00:04:17,720 --> 00:04:20,000
Give yourselves a big round of applause.

58
00:04:20,079 --> 00:04:22,079
Amazing job.

59
00:04:22,160 --> 00:04:24,520
What's today's master class?

60
00:04:24,600 --> 00:04:26,360
What will we be facing today?

61
00:04:26,440 --> 00:04:30,240
It's exciting and new for me. I love it.

62
00:04:30,320 --> 00:04:34,200
We're heading into the first
master class of the season.

63
00:04:34,280 --> 00:04:39,280
Please give a big round of applause
for Mentor Pancake and Mentor Off.

64
00:04:42,200 --> 00:04:44,280
- Hello.
- Hello.

65
00:04:44,360 --> 00:04:46,400
- Hello.
- Hello.

66
00:04:46,480 --> 00:04:47,880
I walked out with Pancake.

67
00:04:47,960 --> 00:04:49,160
I didn't feel pressure

68
00:04:49,240 --> 00:04:52,320
because she has
a really solid theoretical foundation.

69
00:04:52,400 --> 00:04:56,000
She's probably studied this a lot.
What year did she start modeling anyway?

70
00:04:58,680 --> 00:05:00,360
No idea, but it's been a long time.

71
00:05:00,440 --> 00:05:02,120
Right. We'll have to wait and see.

72
00:05:02,880 --> 00:05:05,360
For our first master class,

73
00:05:05,440 --> 00:05:10,520
we'll discuss something crucial
for being professional models.

74
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:13,120
That is your look.

75
00:05:13,200 --> 00:05:15,560
As professional models,

76
00:05:15,640 --> 00:05:18,080
you must be able to adapt your look

77
00:05:18,160 --> 00:05:21,200
to fit any brief and situation.

78
00:05:21,280 --> 00:05:23,800
Therefore, today's master class is…

79
00:05:26,360 --> 00:05:30,240
A look isn't just about
being handsome or beautiful.

80
00:05:30,320 --> 00:05:31,840
It's about being able

81
00:05:31,920 --> 00:05:35,600
to adapt to whatever character
the client wants.

82
00:05:35,680 --> 00:05:39,040
I think, first of all,
it's about keeping your own identity.

83
00:05:39,120 --> 00:05:43,320
You must know what you're doing.
You have to understand the assignment.

84
00:05:43,400 --> 00:05:46,600
What character are you portraying today?
What are you here to do?

85
00:05:46,680 --> 00:05:50,240
Are you an actor, a model,
or a host today?

86
00:05:50,320 --> 00:05:53,720
You need to understand
the brief and your role.

87
00:05:54,560 --> 00:05:56,600
First, you have
to interpret the assignment.

88
00:05:56,680 --> 00:06:00,200
You have to figure out
what your character is for the assignment.

89
00:06:00,280 --> 00:06:04,440
Once you understand the character,
your charisma will naturally show.

90
00:06:04,520 --> 00:06:06,080
Because you know yourselves,

91
00:06:06,160 --> 00:06:08,640
and you understand the assigned character.

92
00:06:08,720 --> 00:06:11,280
I want you all to be unique
and have your own style.

93
00:06:11,360 --> 00:06:13,480
My uniqueness is a combination of things.

94
00:06:13,560 --> 00:06:17,440
My hair, face, body, and height.
It's very distinct.

95
00:06:17,520 --> 00:06:19,200
I think I'm quite unique.

96
00:06:19,280 --> 00:06:21,320
Today's task is not difficult.

97
00:06:21,400 --> 00:06:25,160
We have five hats for you to try on.

98
00:06:25,240 --> 00:06:30,160
We want to see how you adapt
your character to match each hat.

99
00:06:30,240 --> 00:06:35,160
Having a story in mind
helps you communicate your inner feelings.

100
00:06:35,240 --> 00:06:37,640
You have to blend in with your wardrobe.

101
00:06:37,720 --> 00:06:41,720
If these two go hand in hand,
it works well.

102
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:43,120
You'll be memorable.

103
00:06:43,200 --> 00:06:44,720
Go ahead and pick your hats.

104
00:06:44,800 --> 00:06:47,400
- Don't fight over it.
- Try them on.

105
00:06:47,480 --> 00:06:52,040
When I saw the green bucket hat,
I instantly knew it was mine.

106
00:06:52,120 --> 00:06:53,200
It fits my vibe.

107
00:06:53,280 --> 00:06:54,320
Please step forward.

108
00:06:58,800 --> 00:06:59,960
So cool.

109
00:07:00,040 --> 00:07:02,600
He seems to already understand this hat.

110
00:07:02,680 --> 00:07:03,600
He wears it often.

111
00:07:03,680 --> 00:07:04,880
- I aimed for it.
- Yes.

112
00:07:04,960 --> 00:07:07,200
Easy. I wore it and posed naturally.

113
00:07:07,280 --> 00:07:09,680
Being the first,
I set the standard effortlessly.

114
00:07:09,760 --> 00:07:11,520
The hat suits him best.

115
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:13,560
Bonus looked totally relaxed.

116
00:07:13,640 --> 00:07:17,240
I think he already had an image in mind
before he even picked it up.

117
00:07:17,320 --> 00:07:19,720
That's why he did well
and looked so natural.

118
00:07:19,800 --> 00:07:20,800
Kimhan, your turn.

119
00:07:20,880 --> 00:07:22,920
Oh, a construction foreman look.

120
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:26,840
Actually,
Kimhan took the hat that I wanted.

121
00:07:26,920 --> 00:07:30,640
I think I would be better
at portraying that look and posing.

122
00:07:30,720 --> 00:07:32,840
It's a shame that Kimhan took it first.

123
00:07:34,200 --> 00:07:35,680
It's beige, yes.

124
00:07:37,440 --> 00:07:39,520
Fox had a story in his head like,

125
00:07:39,600 --> 00:07:41,520
"Hey, today is a chill day.

126
00:07:41,600 --> 00:07:43,440
I might wear this to the beach."

127
00:07:43,520 --> 00:07:45,480
- He kept in character.
- He built it up.

128
00:07:45,560 --> 00:07:49,080
He built up the mood
to make the concept clear.

129
00:07:49,160 --> 00:07:51,080
- It works.
- Keeping it cool.

130
00:07:51,160 --> 00:07:53,160
- You came with a story.
- Thank you.

131
00:07:53,240 --> 00:07:55,120
Okay, next is Lincoln.

132
00:07:55,800 --> 00:07:59,560
For the master class, I wasn't sure
what to do. It was so fast.

133
00:07:59,640 --> 00:08:03,800
So I put on the hat and thought,
"Okay, I'm Michael Jackson now."

134
00:08:03,880 --> 00:08:04,720
MJ?

135
00:08:04,800 --> 00:08:06,720
- You can't do ordinary anymore.
- Yes.

136
00:08:07,320 --> 00:08:09,080
Lincoln understood the assignment.

137
00:08:09,160 --> 00:08:11,360
Anyone could tell he was portraying
Michael Jackson.

138
00:08:11,440 --> 00:08:14,640
Lincoln had a clear story in mind.

139
00:08:14,720 --> 00:08:19,240
That made us feel,
"Yes, he nailed it with this hat."

140
00:08:19,320 --> 00:08:20,760
Next, Pom.

141
00:08:21,640 --> 00:08:24,480
Pom chose a difficult hat,
but he handled it well.

142
00:08:24,560 --> 00:08:26,320
It's a pass for me.

143
00:08:26,400 --> 00:08:29,960
I'm very surprised.
They did better than expected.

144
00:08:30,040 --> 00:08:34,200
There wasn't much confusion.
I got to see how each of them performs.

145
00:08:34,280 --> 00:08:36,600
Most importantly,
maintaining your identity

146
00:08:36,679 --> 00:08:40,559
while adapting to different things
should go hand in hand.

147
00:08:40,640 --> 00:08:44,039
That's how you bring out
your full potential

148
00:08:44,120 --> 00:08:47,480
while staying true to yourselves.

149
00:08:47,560 --> 00:08:48,760
Mew.

150
00:08:49,760 --> 00:08:50,960
At first, I had…

151
00:08:51,600 --> 00:08:54,560
a magazine cover in mind
with the outfit and everything.

152
00:08:54,640 --> 00:08:57,320
But it turned out looking like
a soybean on my head.

153
00:08:58,440 --> 00:09:01,000
I was confused. Perhaps not.

154
00:09:01,080 --> 00:09:02,680
Next person.

155
00:09:02,760 --> 00:09:03,600
Peem.

156
00:09:07,760 --> 00:09:08,840
Is this…

157
00:09:09,640 --> 00:09:11,440
a photoshoot, or is there a story?

158
00:09:11,520 --> 00:09:12,920
It was a hiking vibe.

159
00:09:14,800 --> 00:09:17,480
- Fashionable.
- We know it's a photoshoot.

160
00:09:17,560 --> 00:09:20,040
But the story wasn't clear.

161
00:09:20,120 --> 00:09:23,440
- We should feel it.
- And understand what you're doing.

162
00:09:23,520 --> 00:09:26,480
You can have a story,
but you need to portray it.

163
00:09:26,560 --> 00:09:31,040
You don't want people to be confused
about what your story is.

164
00:09:31,120 --> 00:09:32,640
Some got it, some were confused.

165
00:09:32,720 --> 00:09:35,240
Some didn't get it, some only had a story.

166
00:09:35,320 --> 00:09:36,760
But you need to have it all.

167
00:09:36,840 --> 00:09:39,280
I know I overthought it during class.

168
00:09:39,360 --> 00:09:41,680
But I won't disappoint you
when the time comes.

169
00:09:41,760 --> 00:09:46,400
It's time to begin our master class.

170
00:09:46,480 --> 00:09:50,440
Today's master class theme
is "Freedom to Move."

171
00:09:50,520 --> 00:09:54,080
Your face must be able
to adapt to various looks

172
00:09:54,160 --> 00:09:55,880
depending on the situation.

173
00:09:55,960 --> 00:09:59,080
Your task today is a photoshoot,

174
00:09:59,160 --> 00:10:01,600
but it's more special
than any still photoshoot.

175
00:10:01,680 --> 00:10:06,880
We want a '60s retro fashion shoot.

176
00:10:06,960 --> 00:10:09,040
A photoshoot? Personally, it's…

177
00:10:11,800 --> 00:10:12,640
a piece of cake.

178
00:10:14,160 --> 00:10:16,840
Please welcome Puii, Wanisa Duangjinda,

179
00:10:16,920 --> 00:10:19,600
Managing Director of Bearbeary Group.

180
00:10:19,680 --> 00:10:20,960
A fashion brand owner

181
00:10:21,040 --> 00:10:24,400
who understands the design
and lifestyle of the new generation.

182
00:10:24,480 --> 00:10:26,640
She makes jeans
into more than just clothes,

183
00:10:26,720 --> 00:10:29,320
but a look that enhances your true self.

184
00:10:31,920 --> 00:10:33,360
- Hello.
- Hello.

185
00:10:33,840 --> 00:10:36,840
WANISA DUANGJINDA
MANAGING DIRECTOR OF BEARBEARY GROUP

186
00:10:36,920 --> 00:10:40,360
Hello everyone, and congratulations
to these 15 young men.

187
00:10:40,440 --> 00:10:42,480
I'm very honored

188
00:10:42,560 --> 00:10:44,560
to co-create the challenge

189
00:10:44,640 --> 00:10:48,440
for the first master class
of <i>The Face Men Season 4</i>.

190
00:10:48,520 --> 00:10:51,720
Bearbeary has prepared
a fashion editorial photoshoot

191
00:10:51,800 --> 00:10:55,840
to test your ability to pull off
different looks with our jeans.

192
00:10:55,920 --> 00:11:00,040
Previously,
Bearbeary only made women's jeans

193
00:11:00,120 --> 00:11:01,840
and received great feedback.

194
00:11:01,920 --> 00:11:05,200
This year, we're launching
our first men's collection

195
00:11:05,280 --> 00:11:10,520
right here on <i>The Face Men</i>
for the first time.

196
00:11:10,600 --> 00:11:15,080
I feel so lucky to be among the men
launching this collection.

197
00:11:15,160 --> 00:11:17,680
Wearing their jeans is very special.

198
00:11:17,760 --> 00:11:19,880
We're the first, so I have to brag a bit.

199
00:11:19,960 --> 00:11:23,680
I'm going to win today
and take a pair home for sure.

200
00:11:25,080 --> 00:11:28,640
Today, Bearbeary brought our first series,
the Relax series,

201
00:11:28,720 --> 00:11:31,520
for you to wear in this photoshoot.

202
00:11:31,600 --> 00:11:34,760
These jeans use
special weaving technology.

203
00:11:34,840 --> 00:11:37,960
The fabric is smooth,
sleek, and well-fitting.

204
00:11:38,040 --> 00:11:40,840
The fabric offers superior stretch
compared with regular jeans.

205
00:11:40,920 --> 00:11:45,200
This allows it to fit any body type
and create a variety of looks.

206
00:11:45,280 --> 00:11:48,040
For today's master class,

207
00:11:48,120 --> 00:11:52,600
we have a professional photographer
joining us to shoot your campaigns.

208
00:11:52,680 --> 00:11:58,040
Please give a big round of applause
to Oak, Napat Gunkham.

209
00:12:01,720 --> 00:12:04,240
NAPAT GUNKHAM
EDITORIAL PHOTOGRAPHER

210
00:12:04,320 --> 00:12:06,960
We'll be shooting a fashion editorial.

211
00:12:07,040 --> 00:12:12,360
All contestants will take
both duo shots and group shots today.

212
00:12:12,440 --> 00:12:13,760
Let's get to work.

213
00:12:13,840 --> 00:12:15,560
But there's a special twist.

214
00:12:15,640 --> 00:12:20,520
You'll be taking your duo shots
with professional female models.

215
00:12:20,600 --> 00:12:25,760
Wow, okay.
Now, I'm totally motivated for the shoot.

216
00:12:25,840 --> 00:12:29,040
I'm a bit nervous
about shooting with women.

217
00:12:29,120 --> 00:12:32,480
I guess it will just be
business as usual, right?

218
00:12:32,560 --> 00:12:34,480
I can't wait. It's going to be fun.

219
00:12:34,560 --> 00:12:38,440
Please give a big round of applause
for our professional female models.

220
00:12:38,520 --> 00:12:42,200
MellaMay, Gail, Lita, and Palmy.

221
00:12:43,720 --> 00:12:47,960
The girls from <i>The Face Thailand Season 6.</i>

222
00:12:48,040 --> 00:12:50,840
I'm so excited.
The energy was at 100% just now.

223
00:12:50,920 --> 00:12:54,200
I was feeling tired,
but once they walked in, I was wide awake.

224
00:12:56,840 --> 00:12:59,400
It's getting hot!
It's getting hot in here!

225
00:12:59,480 --> 00:13:00,800
As for the group shots,

226
00:13:00,880 --> 00:13:04,680
we'll divide you into four groups
with one female model each,

227
00:13:04,760 --> 00:13:07,560
featuring one series of Bearbeary jeans.

228
00:13:07,640 --> 00:13:11,200
The duo shots must look cool, relaxed,

229
00:13:11,280 --> 00:13:12,680
and masculine.

230
00:13:12,760 --> 00:13:17,280
The group shots must clearly express
the character of each series.

231
00:13:17,360 --> 00:13:20,960
Here are the rules for this master class.

232
00:13:21,040 --> 00:13:26,160
Each contestant must take one duo shot
with a female model.

233
00:13:26,240 --> 00:13:28,960
You'll only have one minute.

234
00:13:29,040 --> 00:13:33,200
After that, you must take
one group shot per team.

235
00:13:33,280 --> 00:13:36,400
You'll have two minutes per team.

236
00:13:36,480 --> 00:13:39,480
You must direct the poses and composition

237
00:13:39,560 --> 00:13:41,200
for all four female models.

238
00:13:41,280 --> 00:13:45,520
