I feel so bad for Gail.

499
00:25:15,040 --> 00:25:19,160
She's in the Comfort group,
but she didn't look comfortable.

500
00:25:19,240 --> 00:25:21,360
It involves doing the splits.

501
00:25:21,440 --> 00:25:24,720
It's about being flexible
during activities.

502
00:25:24,800 --> 00:25:26,360
You need to do more than that.

503
00:25:26,440 --> 00:25:28,440
Now, for the last group, the Cool group.

504
00:25:28,520 --> 00:25:30,640
Please welcome our model, MellaMay.

505
00:25:30,720 --> 00:25:33,680
Our first contestant in this group is Pom.

506
00:25:35,320 --> 00:25:40,320
I briefed MellaMay
on the mood and poses I wanted.

507
00:25:40,400 --> 00:25:43,480
And we only had
a limited time of one minute.

508
00:25:43,560 --> 00:25:45,920
I was a little frantic.

509
00:25:46,000 --> 00:25:47,080
Time starts now.

510
00:25:48,520 --> 00:25:50,400
Beautiful. No kidding.

511
00:25:53,520 --> 00:25:54,560
Here we go.

512
00:25:57,840 --> 00:25:59,760
- You guys can talk.
- Ten seconds left.

513
00:25:59,840 --> 00:26:01,080
- Communicate.
- Fun to watch.

514
00:26:01,160 --> 00:26:03,560
We talked at first, but we found our flow.

515
00:26:03,640 --> 00:26:04,760
We finally clicked.

516
00:26:04,840 --> 00:26:07,040
We really synced up towards the end.

517
00:26:07,120 --> 00:26:08,520
Next up is Wigrom.

518
00:26:13,600 --> 00:26:15,200
They seem a bit disconnected.

519
00:26:16,280 --> 00:26:18,440
They're doing their own thing.

520
00:26:18,520 --> 00:26:19,360
Right.

521
00:26:19,440 --> 00:26:21,880
Come together, pose together.

522
00:26:21,960 --> 00:26:25,200
- Communicate, Wigrom.
- Twenty seconds left.

523
00:26:25,280 --> 00:26:27,600
You need to interact. I can't see…

524
00:26:27,680 --> 00:26:29,520
It's like you're in separate shoots.

525
00:26:29,600 --> 00:26:33,160
To be honest,
Wigrom was a bit confused too.

526
00:26:33,240 --> 00:26:34,680
He didn't know what to do.

527
00:26:34,760 --> 00:26:37,680
He didn't have a clear idea
for the female model.

528
00:26:37,760 --> 00:26:40,000
He couldn't communicate
exactly how to pose.

529
00:26:40,800 --> 00:26:43,040
The ultimate goal is to sell the pants.

530
00:26:43,120 --> 00:26:44,240
To sell the pants.

531
00:26:44,320 --> 00:26:45,440
To sell the pants.

532
00:26:45,520 --> 00:26:47,080
"To sell the pants." That's it.

533
00:26:47,160 --> 00:26:49,840
I panicked
because my arm got stuck in the shirt.

534
00:26:49,920 --> 00:26:53,000
But I think I did the best I could.

535
00:26:53,080 --> 00:26:54,200
I really tried.

536
00:26:54,280 --> 00:26:57,560
Let's move on to the last contestant
in the Cool group.

537
00:26:57,640 --> 00:26:58,520
Leo.

538
00:27:03,080 --> 00:27:05,440
Leo Oppa has a great body, obviously.

539
00:27:05,520 --> 00:27:07,680
He showed off his body
more than the pants.

540
00:27:07,760 --> 00:27:10,280
Crew over there, keep it down, please.

541
00:27:10,360 --> 00:27:13,120
Since Leo came out,
the crew has been so annoying.

542
00:27:13,200 --> 00:27:16,440
They seem to be cheering him on
extra hard.

543
00:27:17,720 --> 00:27:19,200
Calm down, girls.

544
00:27:23,720 --> 00:27:24,640
Time starts now.

545
00:27:28,160 --> 00:27:29,480
- Oh, wow!
- Oh, wow!

546
00:27:29,560 --> 00:27:30,920
Oh, wow!

547
00:27:35,440 --> 00:27:40,680
None of us thought a deep squat pose
would look good.

548
00:27:40,760 --> 00:27:43,400
I couldn't imagine how it would turn out.

549
00:27:44,600 --> 00:27:45,440
Beautiful.

550
00:27:45,960 --> 00:27:47,560
- Oh my god.
- Goodness.

551
00:27:51,200 --> 00:27:53,200
Oh, it's raining!

552
00:27:54,200 --> 00:27:56,800
The Cool style is very simple.

553
00:27:56,880 --> 00:28:00,080
You don't have to overthink it.
Can you do splits like me?

554
00:28:01,120 --> 00:28:03,920
And now, we're moving on
to the group shots.

555
00:28:04,000 --> 00:28:05,600
The first group, Soft, you're up.

556
00:28:05,680 --> 00:28:09,120
You only have two minutes.

557
00:28:09,200 --> 00:28:11,880
If you're ready, time starts now.

558
00:28:12,960 --> 00:28:17,560
Going first is definitely stressful.
But we already planned out what to do.

559
00:28:17,640 --> 00:28:19,840
- Get in behind.
- Give me a hand.

560
00:28:21,080 --> 00:28:24,160
- Can you lift your leg? Lift it up.
- Lift my leg?

561
00:28:24,240 --> 00:28:26,280
Like you guys are carrying a <i>Naga </i>serpent.

562
00:28:26,360 --> 00:28:29,800
- Old photo that they carried the <i>Naga</i>.
- I wouldn't dare say it.

563
00:28:30,560 --> 00:28:34,360
I think the shot of them carrying Lita
was a bit too much.

564
00:28:34,440 --> 00:28:38,000
The composition might not look
beautiful or perfect.

565
00:28:38,080 --> 00:28:41,240
Let's move on to the next group.
The Relax group.

566
00:28:41,320 --> 00:28:42,920
- Relax.
- You can brief her now.

567
00:28:43,000 --> 00:28:45,160
- Okay, let's go.
- You have two minutes.

568
00:28:45,240 --> 00:28:46,280
- What do we do?
- Start.

569
00:28:46,360 --> 00:28:48,000
Interact with whoever you pick.

570
00:28:48,080 --> 00:28:50,120
Good.

571
00:28:50,200 --> 00:28:52,520
- Good.
- For the group shot,

572
00:28:52,600 --> 00:28:56,960
my initial strategy was to plan the levels
of who stands up and who squats down.

573
00:28:57,040 --> 00:28:58,640
You guys are out of frame.

574
00:28:58,720 --> 00:29:01,440
Only 50 seconds left.

575
00:29:01,520 --> 00:29:04,280
- What is this?
- You're blocking each other.

576
00:29:04,360 --> 00:29:05,960
Guys, work together.

577
00:29:06,040 --> 00:29:08,280
Do you want to sit? Should someone sit?

578
00:29:08,360 --> 00:29:11,120
- Come on, guys, do something.
- Thirty seconds.

579
00:29:11,200 --> 00:29:12,520
- Good.
- Now, laugh.

580
00:29:14,560 --> 00:29:17,040
It's not really working, I'm afraid.

581
00:29:17,120 --> 00:29:18,720
I still feel that…

582
00:29:18,800 --> 00:29:22,240
Maybe it's the time limit,
the teamwork, or other things.

583
00:29:22,320 --> 00:29:24,360
It just didn't click. It looked confusing.

584
00:29:24,440 --> 00:29:27,960
Next up is Team Comfort.
Our model is Gail.

585
00:29:28,040 --> 00:29:29,360
Time starts now.

586
00:29:35,760 --> 00:29:38,080
- That's it.
- Ten seconds.

587
00:29:39,400 --> 00:29:40,240
Oh, no.

588
00:29:40,320 --> 00:29:42,680
Obviously, that doesn't look comfortable.

589
00:29:42,760 --> 00:29:45,120
It's obvious.
It's an uncomfortable comfort.

590
00:29:45,200 --> 00:29:48,680
But towards the end,
they started dividing into groups.

591
00:29:48,760 --> 00:29:51,200
Having the model stand in the middle
was refreshing.

592
00:29:51,280 --> 00:29:54,960
But I still don't see the "comfort" in it.

593
00:29:57,760 --> 00:30:00,120
Next up is the Cool group.

594
00:30:00,200 --> 00:30:02,160
- Here, in the middle.
- Time starts now.

595
00:30:02,240 --> 00:30:04,200
Right in the middle, then pose.

596
00:30:04,280 --> 00:30:05,160
What kind of pose?

597
00:30:05,240 --> 00:30:06,240
Hey, that looks good.

598
00:30:06,320 --> 00:30:09,240
Before coming in, we planned our poses.

599
00:30:09,320 --> 00:30:12,440
Time was limited,
so I wanted everything to be…

600
00:30:12,520 --> 00:30:15,320
Let's just have one leader to avoid chaos.

601
00:30:15,400 --> 00:30:16,800
Don't just stand there.

602
00:30:16,880 --> 00:30:19,280
- A group of four is easy to arrange.
- Great.

603
00:30:19,360 --> 00:30:22,440
Since there are four of them,
composing the shot is easier.

604
00:30:22,520 --> 00:30:25,320
I think they'll have plenty of cute shots.

605
00:30:25,920 --> 00:30:26,840
Can he carry you?

606
00:30:26,920 --> 00:30:27,760
- Yes.
- Okay.

607
00:30:28,480 --> 00:30:30,360
Aww!

608
00:30:30,440 --> 00:30:33,080
- Oh, wow.
- Great squat.

609
00:30:33,160 --> 00:30:35,200
- Give me something.
- Last 20 seconds.

610
00:30:35,280 --> 00:30:38,280
We had high hopes for Pom
and wanted him to win.

611
00:30:38,360 --> 00:30:40,800
But once I saw Leo's pose,
it was a clear win for him.

612
00:30:40,880 --> 00:30:44,280
I couldn't imagine how squatting
while carrying a woman…

613
00:30:44,360 --> 00:30:46,960
could possibly look cool.

614
00:30:47,040 --> 00:30:48,560
But Leo pulled it off.

615
00:30:48,640 --> 00:30:52,120
Our contestants just showcased
a variety of looks

616
00:30:52,200 --> 00:30:56,080
presenting Bearbeary's Relax series jeans.

617
00:30:56,160 --> 00:31:00,480
Let's take a look
at the judge's decisions.

618
00:31:00,560 --> 00:31:05,920
Our judge has selected
the three best photos

619
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:07,800
from the duo shot round.

620
00:31:07,880 --> 00:31:10,680
Let's take a look.

621
00:31:12,720 --> 00:31:14,840
Jacob, Rome, and Leo.

622
00:31:16,760 --> 00:31:17,960
I'm thrilled.

623
00:31:18,040 --> 00:31:20,800
Honestly, I expected
to make the top three.

624
00:31:20,880 --> 00:31:24,760
The shot came out
exactly as I pictured it.

625
00:31:24,840 --> 00:31:30,720
Honestly, everyone did well
given the limited time.

626
00:31:30,800 --> 00:31:33,920
There were a few hiccups,
mostly due to the time crunch

627
00:31:34,000 --> 00:31:37,600
which made some
of your poses look a bit off.

628
00:31:37,680 --> 00:31:40,600
But overall, it was great.

629
00:31:40,680 --> 00:31:41,920
I agree with Puii.

630
00:31:42,000 --> 00:31:44,400
Each photo gave off a different vibe.

631
00:31:44,480 --> 00:31:47,800
But they all
clearly highlighted the jeans.

632
00:31:47,880 --> 00:31:52,440
The main goal was to showcase masculinity.
It really shone in the photos.

633
00:31:52,520 --> 00:31:57,680
I think these three photos
perfectly captured that essence.

634
00:31:57,760 --> 00:32:00,800
All right, it's time
to announce the winner.

635
00:32:00,880 --> 00:32:03,960
And today's winner
gets a prize, right, Puii?

636
00:32:04,040 --> 00:32:08,560
Yes, a 10,000-baht prize from Bearbeary.

637
00:32:12,400 --> 00:32:15,440
All right, it's time.

638
00:32:15,520 --> 00:32:21,440
Who was the most outstanding
in this master class's duo shot round?

639
00:32:21,520 --> 00:32:24,640
The most outstanding contestant is…

640
00:32:27,280 --> 00:32:28,200
Rome.

641
00:32:35,760 --> 00:32:39,160
See? I told you I could do it. Period.

642
00:32:39,840 --> 00:32:44,320
He touched my heart.
He really met my expectations. Yes.

643
00:32:44,400 --> 00:32:46,600
That's not all.

644
00:32:46,680 --> 00:32:48,720
We have one more prize

645
00:32:48,800 --> 00:32:52,960
for the most outstanding contestant
in the group shot.

646
00:32:53,040 --> 00:32:56,000
Here are the group shots
from all four groups.

647
00:32:59,280 --> 00:33:01,960
- What do you think of the group shots?
- They're good.

648
00:33:02,040 --> 00:33:06,760
I think they look cute,
and you can really see the teamwork.

649
00:33:06,840 --> 00:33:10,240
Even though you guys struggled
with the posing at first…

650
00:33:10,320 --> 00:33:12,320
everyone managed to pull it together…

651
00:33:12,400 --> 00:33:16,360
and take great, cohesive team photos.

652
00:33:16,440 --> 00:33:18,280
You guys were great and very lovely.

653
00:33:18,360 --> 00:33:21,800
Nailing a group shot
in two minutes isn't easy.

654
00:33:21,880 --> 00:33:25,960
They all did an impressive job
for their first try.

655
00:33:26,040 --> 00:33:30,640
Let's take a look at the best group shot.

656
00:33:31,320 --> 00:33:34,720
The best group shot goes to Cool group.

657
00:33:38,200 --> 00:33:39,800
Great composition.

658
00:33:39,880 --> 00:33:44,000
Everyone's eye contact
with the camera was spot on.

659
00:33:44,080 --> 00:33:46,840
Only one word comes to mind, "cool."

660
00:33:46,920 --> 00:33:48,280
Puii.

661
00:33:48,360 --> 00:33:51,880
Who was the most outstanding contestant
in the group shot round?

662
00:33:51,960 --> 00:33:57,360
The most outstanding contestant
for the group shot is…

663
00:33:59,800 --> 00:34:01,080
Leo.

664
00:34:11,520 --> 00:34:14,679
Our first master class was a lot of fun.

665
00:34:14,760 --> 00:34:16,960
A huge thank you to Puii

666
00:34:17,040 --> 00:34:19,199
for joining our master class today.

667
00:34:19,280 --> 00:34:23,880
As for the challenges that you will face
in the next campaign…

668
00:34:23,960 --> 00:34:25,639
Good luck, everyone.

669
00:34:29,360 --> 00:34:31,719
My kids didn't lose.

670
00:34:31,800 --> 00:34:35,040
If they just hit the brief,
they'll win for sure.

671
00:34:35,120 --> 00:34:36,760
We'll do better.

672
00:34:36,840 --> 00:34:39,239
Ready or not, you just have to do it.

673
00:34:39,320 --> 00:34:41,360
I believe in my team.

674
00:34:51,320 --> 00:34:53,320
We're prepared for the first campaign.

675
00:34:53,400 --> 00:34:55,600
Let's see what we're up against.

676
00:34:55,679 --> 00:34:58,680
We lost the master class,
so we can't lose this.

677
00:34:58,760 --> 00:35:03,400
Welcome to the first campaign
of <i>The Face Men Thailand Season 4</i>.

678
00:35:04,480 --> 00:35:05,480
Yes!

679
00:35:05,560 --> 00:35:07,440
Today, we're at Cloud 11.

680
00:35:07,520 --> 00:35:10,520
The new Creative Destination
in South Sukhumvit.

681
00:35:10,600 --> 00:35:12,960
<i>A space for creators.</i>

682
00:35:13,040 --> 00:35:16,920
<i>Aiming to elevate Thai content creators</i>
<i>to the global stage.</i>

683
00:35:17,000 --> 00:35:20,240
Cloud 11 has a huge courtyard.

684
00:35:20,320 --> 00:35:22,520
I think it can be our runway.

685
00:35:22,600 --> 00:35:24,760
For the first campaign of this season,

686
00:35:25,960 --> 00:35:28,640
you'll be walking the runway.

687
00:35:30,280 --> 00:35:31,160
Right up my alley.

688
00:35:31,240 --> 00:35:34,200
Right here at Cloud 11 Park.

689
00:35:35,000 --> 00:35:38,280
The largest canopied rooftop garden
in Bangkok.

690
00:35:38,360 --> 00:35:42,160
In a campaign called
The Creative Cloud Canvas.

691
00:35:42,240 --> 00:35:46,160
Now, let's meet the person
who will give us today's brief.

692
00:35:46,240 --> 00:35:48,120
Noom, Apiwat Yosprapan

693
00:35:51,520 --> 00:35:53,880
APIWAT YOSPRAPAN
RENOWNED THAI FASHION STYLIST

694
00:35:53,960 --> 00:35:57,240
How does the brief
for The Creative Cloud Canvas go?

695
00:35:57,320 --> 00:35:59,960
- I see this place as a blank canvas.
- Right.

696
00:36:00,040 --> 00:36:02,760
We need to add colors to it.

697
00:36:02,840 --> 00:36:07,160
You'll have to use your creativity
to paint on this canvas.

698
00:36:07,240 --> 00:36:09,640
Express yourselves to the fullest.

699
00:36:09,720 --> 00:36:12,240
Show your courage and attitude.

700
00:36:12,320 --> 00:36:16,280
How you use your body language
and manage the space

701
00:36:16,360 --> 00:36:19,280
to leave a lasting impression.

702
00:36:19,360 --> 00:36:21,200
I'm great at runway walks.

703
00:36:21,280 --> 00:36:23,880
Victory is mine. I can already smell it.

704
00:36:23,960 --> 00:36:28,440
All right, it's time
to pick the performance order.

705
00:36:28,520 --> 00:36:29,560
Rome.

706
00:36:29,640 --> 00:36:33,480
Since you won the master class
from the duo shot round,

707
00:36:33,560 --> 00:36:36,720
which team would you like to start first?

708
00:36:36,800 --> 00:36:38,720
I'll choose…

709
00:36:40,280 --> 00:36:41,920
Mentor Pancake's team.

710
00:36:42,000 --> 00:36:46,040
He picked us to go first
to see the favorites in action.

711
00:36:46,120 --> 00:36:48,680
I won't hold back. Just wait and see.

712
00:36:48,760 --> 00:36:50,080
And the second team, Rome?

713
00:36:50,160 --> 00:36:51,400
Mentor Off's team.

714
00:36:51,480 --> 00:36:54,200
So the third team is Mentor Mile's.

715
00:36:54,280 --> 00:36:57,600
Thanks, Rome. I get more time to prepare.

716
00:36:57,680 --> 00:37:00,400
That's not all the surprises
we have today.

717
00:37:00,480 --> 00:37:02,840
Because we have special guests

718
00:37:02,920 --> 00:37:06,480
who will be working alongside you.

719
00:37:06,560 --> 00:37:08,440
Please give a big hand

720
00:37:08,520 --> 00:37:11,280
for the professional models
from <i>The Face Thailand!</i>

721
00:37:12,920 --> 00:37:15,560
They walked down like
it was Victoria's Secret Fashion Show.

722
00:37:15,640 --> 00:37:16,640
All angels.

723
00:37:16,720 --> 00:37:19,240
Bursting with creativity and energy.

724
00:37:29,600 --> 00:37:32,240
- Palmy.
- Palmy is the first pick.

725
00:37:33,160 --> 00:37:34,000
Gail.

726
00:37:34,080 --> 00:37:35,440
Gail is the second.

727
00:37:35,520 --> 00:37:36,960
And the last one?

728
00:37:37,040 --> 00:37:38,640
Minnie is his last pick.

729
00:37:38,720 --> 00:37:41,800
My team gets Palmy, Gail, and Minnie.

730
00:37:41,880 --> 00:37:43,480
It's like… wow.

731
00:37:43,560 --> 00:37:47,200
Watch out for Mentor Mile's team.

732
00:37:57,000 --> 00:38:00,200
When he turned around,
I was like, "<i>Oppa, here, oppa.</i>"

733
00:38:00,280 --> 00:38:01,160
Mentor Off's team.

734
00:38:04,160 --> 00:38:05,760
Love you, <i>Oppa</i>. Thanks.

735
00:38:05,840 --> 00:38:10,400
Team Off, which three models
do you want to pick?

736
00:38:11,040 --> 00:38:11,880
- Gwang.
- Gwang.

737
00:38:11,960 --> 00:38:12,960
Gwang is the first.

738
00:38:13,040 --> 00:38:15,720
Everyone knows whoever has Gwang
will definitely win.

739
00:38:15,800 --> 00:38:17,200
Fah.

740
00:38:17,280 --> 00:38:18,120
The last pick?

741
00:38:18,200 --> 00:38:19,400
Maaprang.

742
00:38:19,480 --> 00:38:23,720
All three are absolute icons of <i>The Face</i>.

743
00:38:23,800 --> 00:38:26,320
They'd better prepare
for elimination this week.

744
00:38:26,400 --> 00:38:32,640
That means Team Pancake-Ananda
will get Rima, Lita, and June.

745
00:38:32,720 --> 00:38:36,800
We didn't even get to choose.
The ones we wanted went to other teams.

746
00:38:37,600 --> 00:38:38,440
For today,

747
00:38:38,520 --> 00:38:42,360
mentors must create
a creative fashion show

748
00:38:42,440 --> 00:38:46,080
to present the clothing brand, 37°c,

749
00:38:46,160 --> 00:38:49,720
and utilize
the Cloud 11 space effectively.

750
00:38:49,800 --> 00:38:53,120
Your team members
will have 20 minutes to rehearse on set.

751
00:38:53,200 --> 00:38:56,760
The judge will look for
the most captivating show

752
00:38:56,840 --> 00:38:59,920
that best answers the brief.

753
00:39:01,720 --> 00:39:03,480
It's a lot of pressure today.

754
00:39:03,560 --> 00:39:07,040
But my friend is here
to help me out today.

755
00:39:07,120 --> 00:39:09,560
Hold on, Mentor Off.
You didn't come alone?

756
00:39:09,640 --> 00:39:10,840
I brought some help.

757
00:39:10,920 --> 00:39:12,800
That's JingJing. Oh, we're screwed.

758
00:39:12,880 --> 00:39:16,280
JingJing Prariyapit Yu,
Thai Supermodel 2012.

759
00:39:16,360 --> 00:39:17,840
She's my helper today.

760
00:39:17,920 --> 00:39:19,320
That's cheating.

761
00:39:19,400 --> 00:39:22,680
Honestly, I just stick to the games.

762
00:39:22,760 --> 00:39:24,120
I don't like cheating.

763
00:39:24,200 --> 00:39:26,520
The rules didn't say that I couldn't.

764
00:39:26,600 --> 00:39:29,480
So I brought her in. End of story.

765
00:39:29,560 --> 00:39:32,120
Our team only has one mentor.
The others have two.

766
00:39:32,200 --> 00:39:34,640
Two heads are better than one.
It's not fair.

767
00:39:34,720 --> 00:39:35,840
Hey.

768
00:39:36,360 --> 00:39:38,760
- Hello.
- Hello, Mentor Pancake.

769
00:39:38,840 --> 00:39:40,520
I was teary when I saw her face.

770
00:39:46,040 --> 00:39:47,080
It's so reassuring.

771
00:39:47,160 --> 00:39:51,320
I know I'm not
a professional runway model.

772
00:39:51,400 --> 00:39:53,480
And the kids feel reassured too.

773
00:39:53,560 --> 00:39:54,560
Diva is here!

774
00:39:54,640 --> 00:39:55,640
Such a relief.

775
00:39:55,720 --> 00:39:58,400
It really feels like our mom is here.

776
00:39:58,480 --> 00:40:00,400
Mentor Mile is all alone today.

777
00:40:00,480 --> 00:40:01,520
What?

778
00:40:01,600 --> 00:40:05,640
I'm not saying they're playing dirty.
I'm just confused.

779
00:40:05,720 --> 00:40:09,720
I was told for Team A&P,
Pan would only be here for one week.

780
00:40:09,800 --> 00:40:11,840
But this is like our third shoot.

781
00:40:11,920 --> 00:40:14,880
What about me?
I've never directed a runway show.

782
00:40:14,960 --> 00:40:16,360
Call Yoghurt.

783
00:40:16,440 --> 00:40:17,800
Is there time?

784
00:40:17,880 --> 00:40:19,680
JingJing said, "Mile, call Yoghurt."

785
00:40:19,760 --> 00:40:21,840
Yoghurt, what should I do? But…

786
00:40:21,920 --> 00:40:25,200
Three seconds later, they announced
the first team's coaching time.

787
00:40:26,280 --> 00:40:27,720
My Yoghurt just melted away.

788
00:40:31,480 --> 00:40:33,400
Let's flex and be confident. Come on.

789
00:40:33,480 --> 00:40:34,360
Timer, please.

790
00:40:34,440 --> 00:40:36,880
First off, today's concept is about love.

791
00:40:36,960 --> 00:40:38,560
I'll group you guys up.

792
00:40:38,640 --> 00:40:41,440
In the real world,
love comes in many forms.

793
00:40:41,520 --> 00:40:43,480
Women love women.

794
00:40:43,560 --> 00:40:46,840
Men love men. Men love women.

795
00:40:46,920 --> 00:40:49,560
Mile straight up asked me
if I could do Boys' Love.

796
00:40:49,640 --> 00:40:51,000
I had to say yes, right?

797
00:40:51,080 --> 00:40:54,120
I want you two to be Jack and Rose, okay?

798
00:40:54,200 --> 00:40:55,680
Jack and Rose.

799
00:40:55,760 --> 00:40:56,840
Rose opens her arms.

800
00:40:56,920 --> 00:40:58,360
Jack doesn't hesitate.

801
00:40:58,440 --> 00:40:59,920
He steps in, boom.

802
00:41:00,000 --> 00:41:01,960
Cue one. Cue two, look at each other.

803
00:41:02,040 --> 00:41:04,080
- Don't be shy.
- I won't be.

804
00:41:04,160 --> 00:41:05,120
Don't be shy.

805
00:41:05,200 --> 00:41:06,640
Give me <i>Titanic</i>.

806
00:41:08,520 --> 00:41:10,480
I felt a bit awkward.

807
00:41:10,560 --> 00:41:14,120
But doing it gave me a new experience.

808
00:41:14,200 --> 00:41:15,760
If you ask if I'd do it again…

809
00:41:15,840 --> 00:41:17,360
I would rather not.

810
00:41:18,680 --> 00:41:20,640
I mean, I know it's just acting.

811
00:41:20,720 --> 00:41:23,280
I trust whatever Mile decides.

812
00:41:23,360 --> 00:41:26,280
Okay, let's start.
Walk out one by one as planned.

813
00:41:26,360 --> 00:41:30,880
I'm happy with it. Remember,
I had very little time to talk to them.

814
00:41:30,960 --> 00:41:34,400
There's a roleplay element to it,
and they need to get it.

815
00:41:34,480 --> 00:41:36,200
- Time's up.
- Okay, that's a wrap.

816
00:41:40,400 --> 00:41:41,680
I'm so nervous.

817
00:41:41,760 --> 00:41:46,760
I hope none of us gets eliminated
in the first Black Room session.

818
00:41:46,840 --> 00:41:50,000
- Hello.
- Hello.

819
00:41:50,080 --> 00:41:55,640
I told Pan that once we're settled,
I would give her a call.

820
00:41:55,720 --> 00:41:57,760
She was only here briefly
for the rehearsal.

821
00:41:57,840 --> 00:41:59,680
But she helped tremendously.

822
00:41:59,760 --> 00:42:00,920
Our first pair is…

823
00:42:04,040 --> 00:42:06,720
You'll pair up with June. Okay.

824
00:42:06,800 --> 00:42:12,320
We have so little time.
Everyone in Team Panda wants to win.

825
00:42:12,400 --> 00:42:15,800
Nobody wants to be sent
to the Black Room, right?

826
00:42:15,880 --> 00:42:18,440
Go upstairs. Remember your partner.

827
00:42:18,520 --> 00:42:20,640
- You two are going last.
- Got it.

828
00:42:20,720 --> 00:42:22,960
At first, I thought 20 minutes was plenty.

829
00:42:23,040 --> 00:42:25,440
But it actually goes by so fast.

830
00:42:25,520 --> 00:42:27,040
Faster. Faster than that.

831
00:42:27,600 --> 00:42:29,120
You're walking too slowly.

832
00:42:29,200 --> 00:42:32,240
I was a bit worried about myself.

833
00:42:32,320 --> 00:42:35,560
I was afraid I would look too stern.

834
00:42:35,640 --> 00:42:39,080
But I didn't want to force it.
I kept it as natural as possible.

835
00:42:39,160 --> 00:42:40,760
PP and Rima.

836
00:42:40,840 --> 00:42:42,560
You two are already fine.

837
00:42:42,640 --> 00:42:45,360
Fifteen minutes have passed. Let's go.

838
00:42:45,440 --> 00:42:46,760
What can you do in 20?

839
00:42:46,840 --> 00:42:50,840
Waking up and saying good morning
already takes 20 minutes.

840
00:42:50,920 --> 00:42:51,920
Last pair, let's go.

841
00:42:52,520 --> 00:42:55,160
It was a total cardio workout.
Running up and down.

842
00:42:55,240 --> 00:42:56,560
I was getting dizzy.

843
00:42:56,640 --> 00:42:59,040
I saw Ananda sweating bullets.

844
00:42:59,120 --> 00:43:01,880
We were panting.
We ran around, and it was over.

845
00:43:01,960 --> 00:43:04,280
Everyone, remember your places, okay?

846
00:43:04,360 --> 00:43:07,080
Okay, guys. Let's do a dress rehearsal.

847
00:43:07,160 --> 00:43:08,480
Give me some energy.

848
00:43:08,560 --> 00:43:09,960
Get to the back.

849
00:43:10,040 --> 00:43:12,200
<i>Now, I get why 20 minutes go by so fast.</i>

850
00:43:12,280 --> 00:43:14,560
<i>You can barely get anything done.</i>

851
00:43:14,640 --> 00:43:15,520
Start.

852
00:43:15,600 --> 00:43:16,720
Wait for my cue.

853
00:43:16,800 --> 00:43:18,640
We opened with a male-female pair.

854
00:43:18,720 --> 00:43:22,480
I figured Lincoln
wouldn't get overshadowed.

855
00:43:22,560 --> 00:43:23,840
Okay, walk.

856
00:43:23,920 --> 00:43:25,320
Cross paths.

857
00:43:26,440 --> 00:43:28,360
Exit the same way you came.

858
00:43:29,920 --> 00:43:32,520
I admit, I'm a perfectionist.

859
00:43:32,600 --> 00:43:35,480
This is a fashion show,
and I'm focusing on that.

860
00:43:35,560 --> 00:43:37,400
Keep it simple, but do it right.

861
00:43:37,480 --> 00:43:38,880
Look alive, Donut.

862
00:43:38,960 --> 00:43:40,600
Keep the energy up.

863
00:43:40,680 --> 00:43:42,960
Mentor Ananda, I can't keep up.

864
00:43:44,160 --> 00:43:45,840
Watch your shoulder, PP.

865
00:43:47,160 --> 00:43:51,560
It's still tough
walking up and down those stairs.

866
00:43:51,640 --> 00:43:53,720
I've barely ever done it.
So it's difficult.

867
00:43:53,800 --> 00:43:55,880
Come on down for the finale.

868
00:43:57,000 --> 00:44:01,040
Utilize the space.
The brief is all about spatial movement.

869
00:44:01,120 --> 00:44:03,800
Hit the brief,
so we can focus on the models.

870
00:44:03,880 --> 00:44:05,080
We didn't have the time.

871
00:44:05,160 --> 00:44:08,200
Whenever we tried to adjust
or focus on them,

872
00:44:08,280 --> 00:44:09,160
time was up.

873
00:44:12,600 --> 00:44:14,920
- Hello.
- Hello.

874
00:44:15,000 --> 00:44:18,120
We'll start the pattern from the top.
Head upstairs.

875
00:44:18,200 --> 00:44:20,480
It was stressful because I didn't prepare.

876
00:44:20,560 --> 00:44:22,400
It was my first time doing this too.

877
00:44:22,480 --> 00:44:24,640
Rome should be up front. Yes?

878
00:44:24,720 --> 00:44:26,200
The two tall ones in front.

879
00:44:26,280 --> 00:44:29,480
Honestly, I was thrilled.
I've never walked as an opener before.

880
00:44:29,560 --> 00:44:31,080
We have different strengths.

881
00:44:31,160 --> 00:44:32,560
JingJing excels at modeling,

882
00:44:32,640 --> 00:44:35,680
while I'm better at placements,
and show concepts.

883
00:44:35,760 --> 00:44:38,920
When we combine those skills,
it works out perfectly.

884
00:44:39,000 --> 00:44:41,960
Maaprang will strike a pose.
Make it a big one.

885
00:44:42,040 --> 00:44:47,440
I wanted the poses
to really engage the audience.

886
00:44:47,520 --> 00:44:50,040
Eight minutes passed, then ten.

887
00:44:50,120 --> 00:44:53,000
Off and I looked at each other,
"Okay, stick to the plan."

888
00:44:53,080 --> 00:44:55,720
Off went up to brief the team,

889
00:44:55,800 --> 00:44:58,120
and I stayed to watch from down here.

890
00:44:58,200 --> 00:44:59,960
Everything flowed smoothly.

891
00:45:00,040 --> 00:45:02,920
We managed to run through
the whole pattern twice.

892
00:45:03,000 --> 00:45:05,440
Have fun with it! Keep the energy up!

893
00:45:06,320 --> 00:45:08,600
Pick up the pace a little.

894
00:45:08,680 --> 00:45:12,320
Guys. Smile! Use your eyes.
"Look at me. I'm gorgeous."

895
00:45:12,400 --> 00:45:14,080
"Look at me. Buy my outfit."

896
00:45:14,680 --> 00:45:18,080
During the blocking rehearsal,
everything was crisp and clear.

897
00:45:18,160 --> 00:45:20,240
It was all very easy to understand.

898
00:45:20,320 --> 00:45:21,600
Today is our day.

899
00:45:21,680 --> 00:45:25,560
Both mentors helped
draw out our full potential.

900
00:45:26,160 --> 00:45:27,080
Strike a pose.

901
00:45:27,760 --> 00:45:30,600
We're stressed, and we tried our best.

902
00:45:30,680 --> 00:45:32,000
I saw everyone's devotion,

903
00:45:32,080 --> 00:45:34,760
not just the team members,
but the crew who helped too.

904
00:45:34,840 --> 00:45:38,120
They worked hard
because they wanted us to win.

905
00:45:38,200 --> 00:45:39,160
Upstairs, start.

906
00:45:40,960 --> 00:45:42,440
Five minutes.

907
00:45:42,520 --> 00:45:44,520
I felt everyone giving it their all.

908
00:45:44,600 --> 00:45:47,800
The 20 minutes we had to practice
flew by so fast.

909
00:45:47,880 --> 00:45:49,720
Enough for one more run-through.

910
00:45:49,800 --> 00:45:52,360
Hurry! Last three minutes left.

911
00:45:52,440 --> 00:45:54,120
Come on out!

912
00:45:55,360 --> 00:45:58,360
Here we go. What are you trying to sell?

913
00:45:58,440 --> 00:46:00,320
Off told me right from the start,

914
00:46:00,400 --> 00:46:01,720
"Jing, have it your way,

915
00:46:01,800 --> 00:46:04,680
but I want you
to stand up there at the end."

916
00:46:04,760 --> 00:46:06,200
Get everyone together.

917
00:46:06,280 --> 00:46:07,840
Go dance up there and wait! Go!

918
00:46:07,920 --> 00:46:09,760
Once you're in position, start dancing!

919
00:46:09,840 --> 00:46:11,880
Great job! Very good!

920
00:46:12,960 --> 00:46:14,840
Energy! Have fun!

921
00:46:15,960 --> 00:46:17,800
Interact with your partners!

922
00:46:17,880 --> 00:46:20,280
It's looking good. Perfect, actually.

923
00:46:21,280 --> 00:46:22,720
What do the other teams have?

924
00:46:22,800 --> 00:46:26,240
I don't know if this exactly meets
the brief they gave us,

925
00:46:26,320 --> 00:46:27,760
but this is how I'm doing it.

926
00:46:37,720 --> 00:46:40,680
Welcome back
to The Creative Cloud Canvas campaign,

927
00:46:40,760 --> 00:46:42,240
here at Cloud 11 Park.

928
00:46:42,320 --> 00:46:45,920
And joining us to judge this campaign,
our first guest

929
00:46:46,000 --> 00:46:49,960
is a leading designer
who is legendary across the industry.

930
00:46:50,040 --> 00:46:53,200
He's also a former mentor
here on <i>The Face</i>.

931
00:46:53,280 --> 00:46:54,720
He was my mentor.

932
00:46:54,800 --> 00:46:57,040
Moo, Asava founder, Polpat Asavaprapha!

933
00:46:58,560 --> 00:46:59,640
- Hello, Daddy.
- Hello.

934
00:47:01,840 --> 00:47:04,840
POLPAT ASAVAPRAPHA
PERSONAL STYLIST, ASAVA FOUNDER

935
00:47:04,920 --> 00:47:08,400
Our second judge is a true styling icon.

936
00:47:08,480 --> 00:47:12,440
He's the creative director
for the brand 37°c,

937
00:47:12,520 --> 00:47:15,400
whose clothes
our contestants are wearing today.

938
00:47:15,480 --> 00:47:18,880
He brought us a collection
called The Equator.

939
00:47:18,960 --> 00:47:22,680
Give a big round of applause
for Pu, Chamnan Pakdeesuk.

940
00:47:24,360 --> 00:47:27,760
CHAMNAN PAKDEESUK
LEGENDARY FASHION DESIGNER, 37°C FOUNDER

941
00:47:27,840 --> 00:47:31,120
And of course, we have two other judges

942
00:47:31,200 --> 00:47:32,680
who need no introduction.

943
00:47:32,760 --> 00:47:35,120
Master Mentor Adam and Royal Mom!

944
00:47:35,200 --> 00:47:37,640
Welcome to today's campaign.

945
00:47:40,920 --> 00:47:43,720
This is the very first campaign
of the season.

946
00:47:43,800 --> 00:47:44,840
If everyone is ready,

947
00:47:44,920 --> 00:47:48,920
let's begin
The Creative Cloud Canvas campaign!

948
00:47:50,920 --> 00:47:54,200
Starting off with our first team,
Team Pancake-Ananda!

949
00:47:54,280 --> 00:47:57,280
My thought for today
was just to keep it simple.

950
00:47:57,360 --> 00:47:59,760
We focused on the fashion
and doing it right.

951
00:47:59,840 --> 00:48:03,520
That's exactly what I wanted to see
from the team.

952
00:48:10,000 --> 00:48:13,360
Choosing Pancake
and Ananda's team to go first

953
00:48:13,440 --> 00:48:14,520
was a very smart move.

954
00:48:14,600 --> 00:48:17,400
This is the first campaign.
We shouldn't go first.

955
00:48:20,000 --> 00:48:21,560
We opened with a man and a woman.

956
00:48:25,000 --> 00:48:26,320
June walks really well.

957
00:48:26,400 --> 00:48:30,400
All the women have actually been
professional models for a while.

958
00:48:31,960 --> 00:48:34,760
I feel like Lincoln won't be overshadowed.

959
00:48:34,840 --> 00:48:37,000
He's naturally confident.

960
00:48:37,080 --> 00:48:38,800
He could handle himself well.

961
00:48:42,200 --> 00:48:47,360
I've never walked
or done anything like this. It's fun.

962
00:48:47,440 --> 00:48:50,360
- They're heading down.
- Keep them coming.

963
00:48:50,440 --> 00:48:52,120
Don't leave a gap.

964
00:48:52,200 --> 00:48:54,200
Why use the walkie-talkie?

965
00:48:54,280 --> 00:48:57,400
How will it help
when you already told them to go?

966
00:48:59,600 --> 00:49:01,760
Cue three is heading down.

967
00:49:02,920 --> 00:49:06,440
I feel so proud.
The energy is great today.

968
00:49:08,080 --> 00:49:09,440
Hey, this is actually good.

969
00:49:09,520 --> 00:49:10,440
Don't talk.

970
00:49:11,080 --> 00:49:12,800
I can barely breathe.

971
00:49:12,880 --> 00:49:15,720
This is great. You're happy.

972
00:49:16,400 --> 00:49:17,240
Wigrom…

973
00:49:17,320 --> 00:49:20,880
Expectations for him aren't very high.

974
00:49:20,960 --> 00:49:22,840
Plus, he's an extra member on the team.

975
00:49:22,920 --> 00:49:26,480
I'm usually lazy and stay home.
I've never done this.

976
00:49:26,560 --> 00:49:28,680
But I like this kind of pressure.

977
00:49:28,760 --> 00:49:30,560
It's challenging. I'll fight.

978
00:49:33,160 --> 00:49:35,000
Cue four is heading down.

979
00:49:35,880 --> 00:49:39,440
During the actual walk,
we didn't follow the practiced route.

980
00:49:39,520 --> 00:49:40,960
And that made me anxious.

981
00:49:41,040 --> 00:49:42,960
- What's his name?
- PP.

982
00:49:43,840 --> 00:49:45,120
He should walk tall.

983
00:49:45,200 --> 00:49:49,920
We chose PP
because he can utilize his acting skills.

984
00:49:50,000 --> 00:49:51,040
He's charismatic.

985
00:49:51,120 --> 00:49:54,280
But he looked pretty stiff when walking.

986
00:49:54,360 --> 00:49:57,040
It's stressful since we're the first team.

987
00:49:57,120 --> 00:49:59,960
And I'm not sure if our route will work.

988
00:50:00,040 --> 00:50:02,760
PP has a very calm personality.

989
00:50:02,840 --> 00:50:06,080
That might make his walk look soft.
So his presence just faded.

990
00:50:06,680 --> 00:50:09,200
It's undeniable that…

991
00:50:09,280 --> 00:50:11,640
a crucial part of being The Face

992
00:50:11,720 --> 00:50:13,000
is the runway walking.

993
00:50:16,640 --> 00:50:19,800
Kimhan really raised the standard
for Ananda and Pancake's show.

994
00:50:19,880 --> 00:50:22,480
Without Kimhan, they might have struggled.

995
00:50:23,520 --> 00:50:25,920
Kimhan keeps improving.

996
00:50:26,000 --> 00:50:29,440
From the day everyone wondered
what was wrong with him.

997
00:50:29,520 --> 00:50:32,320
He did great. He didn't disappoint anyone.

998
00:50:32,400 --> 00:50:36,640
I feel relieved. I'm sure
I didn't walk the same way as before.

999
00:50:36,720 --> 00:50:39,800
And I genuinely feel better.

1000
00:50:39,880 --> 00:50:40,720
So annoying.

1001
00:50:40,800 --> 00:50:42,160
Just kidding.

1002
00:50:42,240 --> 00:50:45,000
He's really talented.

1003
00:50:45,080 --> 00:50:47,600
That's why I wanted him,
but he chose otherwise.

1004
00:50:47,680 --> 00:50:48,560
What can you do?

1005
00:50:48,640 --> 00:50:51,280
Okay, get ready for the finale.

1006
00:50:51,360 --> 00:50:52,800
Tell Kim to speed up a little.

1007
00:51:00,800 --> 00:51:02,680
Beautiful. The walk was decent.

1008
00:51:02,760 --> 00:51:05,080
I'm starting to wonder if we'll win.

1009
00:51:05,160 --> 00:51:07,400
Will my members stay or go?

1010
00:51:13,920 --> 00:51:16,840
Going first is risky.
It can either be great or terrible.

1011
00:51:17,800 --> 00:51:19,800
- They need to use the space well.
- Right.

1012
00:51:20,760 --> 00:51:22,600
Mentors should know how to use the space.

1013
00:51:22,680 --> 00:51:25,480
It's like two separate parts.
They felt disconnected.

1014
00:51:25,560 --> 00:51:27,640
With eight people,
managing the space is tough.

1015
00:51:27,720 --> 00:51:28,560
It is.

1016
00:51:28,640 --> 00:51:30,320
- Plus, there are stairs.
- Right?

1017
00:51:30,400 --> 00:51:32,000
The scaffolding was distracting.

1018
00:51:32,080 --> 00:51:35,360
Honestly, a real fashion show
wouldn't have scaffolding.

1019
00:51:35,440 --> 00:51:36,760
There was also a tree.

1020
00:51:36,840 --> 00:51:38,720
I wanted to cut it down so bad.

1021
00:51:38,800 --> 00:51:41,120
Leave the tree. Just put a camera there.

1022
00:51:41,200 --> 00:51:42,480
So the judges can see.

1023
00:51:42,560 --> 00:51:44,480
Oops, I'm so sorry.

1024
00:51:46,880 --> 00:51:48,560
Out now, Kim, walk out.

1025
00:51:54,720 --> 00:51:57,320
Wow, you said you were stressed.

1026
00:51:57,400 --> 00:51:58,560
I can't breathe.

1027
00:51:58,640 --> 00:51:59,560
Okay.

1028
00:51:59,640 --> 00:52:02,800
Overall, our team did better
than I expected.

1029
00:52:02,880 --> 00:52:05,000
They were perfect. But in their own way.

1030
00:52:08,200 --> 00:52:10,960
That's the first team.
Let's check out the second one.

1031
00:52:11,040 --> 00:52:12,080
Team Off.

1032
00:52:12,160 --> 00:52:14,880
Our theme is Creative Cloud Canvas.

1033
00:52:14,960 --> 00:52:17,880
We made it as creative as possible.
No ordinary walk.

1034
00:52:22,560 --> 00:52:25,160
Give it energy. Be happy.

1035
00:52:25,240 --> 00:52:27,520
Yes. The mentor is hyping them up now.

1036
00:52:31,000 --> 00:52:33,840
Off did a great job boosting their energy
before the walk.

1037
00:52:33,920 --> 00:52:35,960
It really boosted their energy.

1038
00:52:36,040 --> 00:52:38,440
We started with all of them
walking out together.

1039
00:52:38,520 --> 00:52:41,280
It was pretty nerve-wracking
since they're rookies.

1040
00:52:41,360 --> 00:52:43,960
We had to plan who would open and close.

1041
00:52:47,080 --> 00:52:49,560
Rome is such a natural model.

1042
00:52:49,640 --> 00:52:51,080
He looks fluid and agile.

1043
00:52:51,160 --> 00:52:53,000
Perfect. The clothes look great too.

1044
00:52:53,080 --> 00:52:57,200
My team's outfits were the best.
They fit the vibe perfectly.

1045
00:52:57,280 --> 00:53:01,200
I like it. It's very colorful.
I've always liked colorful things.

1046
00:53:04,000 --> 00:53:06,600
They had everyone
walk down together first.

1047
00:53:06,680 --> 00:53:09,160
Then I noticed how well
they balanced the stage.

1048
00:53:09,240 --> 00:53:10,720
Good pace.

1049
00:53:10,800 --> 00:53:11,720
That's fabulous.

1050
00:53:12,560 --> 00:53:13,600
Fabulous.

1051
00:53:13,680 --> 00:53:15,000
If they don't mess up.

1052
00:53:15,080 --> 00:53:18,680
We had different walking styles,
swapping positions. And the fountain.

1053
00:53:20,800 --> 00:53:21,960
Good, good.

1054
00:53:22,800 --> 00:53:26,600
Walking was very easy for me.
So I thought I did well.

1055
00:53:26,680 --> 00:53:30,040
Pom turned out to be
a surprisingly great catch for me.

1056
00:53:32,320 --> 00:53:35,680
Wow, crisscrossing
like this is pretty cool.

1057
00:53:35,760 --> 00:53:37,920
So perfect, as if they practiced for days.

1058
00:53:38,720 --> 00:53:40,440
- Mew is good.
- His vibe is right.

1059
00:53:40,520 --> 00:53:43,400
The skills aren't quite there,
but the vibe is right.

1060
00:53:44,720 --> 00:53:45,600
I was terrified.

1061
00:53:46,320 --> 00:53:48,640
Just a little bit,
but I was mostly confident.

1062
00:53:50,320 --> 00:53:52,320
Do not take your jacket off, kid.

1063
00:53:52,400 --> 00:53:53,960
The energy was so high today.

1064
00:53:54,040 --> 00:53:56,600
We did better than in rehearsals,
so I'm happy.

1065
00:53:58,160 --> 00:54:00,720
No, don't do that.
This isn't a motor show.

1066
00:54:00,800 --> 00:54:05,440
Off's team wasn't that strong.
I think there were some gaps.

1067
00:54:08,520 --> 00:54:11,080
There was dead air at times.

1068
00:54:11,160 --> 00:54:12,360
Bonus.

1069
00:54:12,440 --> 00:54:15,400
I personally like him
and thought he would stand out.

1070
00:54:15,480 --> 00:54:18,040
I feel like
he was under too much pressure.

1071
00:54:18,120 --> 00:54:20,760
You could see
the lack of confidence on his face.

1072
00:54:22,080 --> 00:54:23,760
It helps that the women are there.

1073
00:54:23,840 --> 00:54:25,840
- The guys are…
- Complete rookies.

1074
00:54:25,920 --> 00:54:27,040
No.

1075
00:54:30,080 --> 00:54:32,440
I'm not worried about Rome and Pom.

1076
00:54:32,520 --> 00:54:34,360
The rest are a concern.

1077
00:54:34,440 --> 00:54:36,920
Honestly,
I don't have much runway experience.

1078
00:54:37,000 --> 00:54:39,960
Rome and Pom are good.
They have a lot of experience.

1079
00:54:40,040 --> 00:54:44,360
As for me, I just tried to focus
on my walk and my poses.

1080
00:54:44,440 --> 00:54:46,840
I couldn't see
the big picture like they could.

1081
00:54:47,480 --> 00:54:49,280
We were at the stairs for a short time.

1082
00:54:49,360 --> 00:54:51,520
Then we had to walk up the stairs.

1083
00:54:53,040 --> 00:54:55,000
Fox, who are you looking at?

1084
00:54:55,760 --> 00:54:57,560
Yes. He was…

1085
00:54:57,640 --> 00:54:59,960
I want them to succeed.
I want them to be good.

1086
00:55:00,040 --> 00:55:02,280
I feel like they need to push
themselves more.

1087
00:55:02,360 --> 00:55:04,600
All five of you have to stand out,
not just two.

1088
00:55:09,200 --> 00:55:10,360
They're dancing too.

1089
00:55:12,240 --> 00:55:14,920
The story is about having fun
and enjoying ourselves.

1090
00:55:15,000 --> 00:55:16,760
How do we get them to buy into us?

1091
00:55:17,520 --> 00:55:18,920
My team was the most fun.

1092
00:55:23,560 --> 00:55:25,680
Our team was just so good.

1093
00:55:25,760 --> 00:55:28,680
The characters were very clear.
Bam, bam. One, two, three.

1094
00:55:28,760 --> 00:55:30,560
- Does it end like this?
- Maybe.

1095
00:55:30,640 --> 00:55:33,080
Wow, they're dancing on the scaffolding.

1096
00:55:33,640 --> 00:55:34,720
It was being blocked.

1097
00:55:34,800 --> 00:55:38,840
Our judges today have X-ray vision.
They can see right through it.

1098
00:55:38,920 --> 00:55:40,200
Right through the tree.

1099
00:55:41,760 --> 00:55:43,560
Walking up in heels was hard.

1100
00:55:43,640 --> 00:55:47,040
Fah walked up and seemed to trip a little.

1101
00:55:47,120 --> 00:55:49,360
Was I afraid? The stairs were this narrow.

1102
00:55:49,440 --> 00:55:51,520
It's quite hard for women in heels.

1103
00:55:51,600 --> 00:55:54,760
The stairs have gaps,
and the heels could get stuck there.

1104
00:55:54,840 --> 00:55:57,720
I was going to help,
but they fixed it so fast.

1105
00:55:57,800 --> 00:55:59,640
It's normal. There were no accidents.

1106
00:55:59,720 --> 00:56:01,000
Beautiful choreography.

1107
00:56:01,520 --> 00:56:04,120
The only things that stood out
were the mistakes.

1108
00:56:04,200 --> 00:56:06,640
I can't lose. We hit it perfectly.

1109
00:56:06,720 --> 00:56:09,720
We will win, a hundred percent.
One hundred and ten percent.

1110
00:56:11,280 --> 00:56:13,880
Off, how did you make this in 20 minutes?

1111
00:56:13,960 --> 00:56:17,160
They did so many things.
It was a mix of everything.

1112
00:56:17,240 --> 00:56:20,200
It's good, but I'm not sure.
It felt more like an event.

1113
00:56:20,280 --> 00:56:23,080
I don't know if it fits the brief or not.

1114
00:56:23,160 --> 00:56:25,480
But it was my version of Cloud 11.

1115
00:56:27,600 --> 00:56:28,760
Next team, please.

1116
00:56:28,840 --> 00:56:30,560
Mentor Mile's team.

1117
00:56:30,640 --> 00:56:33,200
The Creative Cloud Canvas.

1118
00:56:33,280 --> 00:56:35,360
I interpret it as love.
Or heaven on earth.

1119
00:56:36,840 --> 00:56:40,400
And based on the location's style,
we should go with something romantic.

1120
00:56:40,480 --> 00:56:42,000
I feel sorry for Mile.

1121
00:56:42,080 --> 00:56:44,960
Mile has never put on
a fashion show before.

1122
00:56:45,040 --> 00:56:47,520
And he's working alone.
He has no one to consult.

1123
00:56:47,600 --> 00:56:49,720
We can only count on ourselves
to push ourselves.

1124
00:56:51,440 --> 00:56:55,040
Freedom of thought and freedom to live
are important to me.

1125
00:56:59,080 --> 00:57:00,040
What is this?

1126
00:57:00,120 --> 00:57:01,080
There's a scene.

1127
00:57:01,160 --> 00:57:03,760
- What is it?
- At the top.

1128
00:57:04,440 --> 00:57:06,400
There's a storyline.

1129
00:57:06,480 --> 00:57:07,920
This team is storytelling.

1130
00:57:08,000 --> 00:57:09,120
It's <i>Titanic</i>.

1131
00:57:09,200 --> 00:57:12,240
A grounded romance
about two men finding love.

1132
00:57:15,000 --> 00:57:15,960
Jack and Rose.

1133
00:57:17,480 --> 00:57:19,880
Oh, it's like a performance.

1134
00:57:19,960 --> 00:57:21,800
That's a surprise. Very abstract.

1135
00:57:22,840 --> 00:57:24,360
New. This is really new.

1136
00:57:24,440 --> 00:57:26,920
I respect their bold move.

1137
00:57:27,000 --> 00:57:29,640
I thought we had it.
But this is the real deal.

1138
00:57:29,720 --> 00:57:32,000
- Way better.
- How did he come up with this?

1139
00:57:32,800 --> 00:57:35,520
Magic would happen
when the timing was right.

1140
00:57:35,600 --> 00:57:36,480
We had to do it.

1141
00:57:37,120 --> 00:57:38,400
And it turned out great.

1142
00:57:38,480 --> 00:57:41,560
I'm not sure if they noticed
when our eyes met.

1143
00:57:41,640 --> 00:57:42,920
So beautiful.

1144
00:57:43,000 --> 00:57:45,680
- The pose speaks for itself.
- Yes, exactly.

1145
00:57:45,760 --> 00:57:47,160
- Perfect attitude.
- Yes.

1146
00:57:47,240 --> 00:57:50,840
We wanted the show to be striking.

1147
00:57:51,800 --> 00:57:55,240
We were so lucky to go last.
The light hit this angle perfectly.

1148
00:57:55,320 --> 00:57:57,200
Way better than spotlights.

1149
00:57:57,280 --> 00:57:59,400
It made everything look natural.

1150
00:57:59,480 --> 00:58:02,920
They showed off the location
and the clothes at the same time.

1151
00:58:06,280 --> 00:58:07,640
Wait, who's this?

1152
00:58:07,720 --> 00:58:09,680
He's Korean. His name is Leo.

1153
00:58:09,760 --> 00:58:10,880
He's a native Korean.

1154
00:58:10,960 --> 00:58:12,600
- He doesn't speak Thai.
- Oh, okay.

1155
00:58:12,680 --> 00:58:14,080
- This one?
- He's handsome.

1156
00:58:14,160 --> 00:58:16,760
Cinderella and the glass slipper.

1157
00:58:19,280 --> 00:58:20,320
Cinderella?

1158
00:58:20,400 --> 00:58:23,680
I thought her heel just broke.

1159
00:58:23,760 --> 00:58:25,440
What made her a Cinderella?

1160
00:58:25,520 --> 00:58:29,000
Because he held the shoe
and put it on her like in <i>Cinderella</i>.

1161
00:58:29,080 --> 00:58:30,440
I thought it would be cute.

1162
00:58:30,520 --> 00:58:32,560
Sorry. I really couldn't tell.

1163
00:58:32,640 --> 00:58:34,800
- Is that Palmy?
- She's talented.

1164
00:58:34,880 --> 00:58:36,400
She's a pro. She can do anything.

1165
00:58:36,480 --> 00:58:41,040
We got lucky.
Palmy really connected with Leo.

1166
00:58:41,120 --> 00:58:42,160
That's destiny.

1167
00:58:47,600 --> 00:58:49,160
Oh, they have Minnie.

1168
00:58:49,240 --> 00:58:51,000
- She's from last season.
- That's Gail.

1169
00:58:51,680 --> 00:58:53,080
It's so Broadway.

1170
00:58:54,800 --> 00:58:56,440
Let's see.

1171
00:58:56,520 --> 00:58:59,960
No offense,
but when you put it all together,

1172
00:59:00,040 --> 00:59:02,400
I don't know where to focus.

1173
00:59:03,440 --> 00:59:05,760
It doesn't really flow well.

1174
00:59:05,840 --> 00:59:08,560
Everything was fighting for attention.

1175
00:59:08,640 --> 00:59:10,840
Personally, I'm not feeling it.

1176
00:59:10,920 --> 00:59:13,680
- It's visually overwhelming.
- Agree.

1177
00:59:13,760 --> 00:59:15,680
Maybe there's too much going on.

1178
00:59:15,760 --> 00:59:18,280
No one told me it was a stage play.

1179
00:59:18,360 --> 00:59:19,680
It's a fashion show.

1180
00:59:19,760 --> 00:59:21,840
- Like…
- It's up to what the judges prefer.

1181
00:59:21,920 --> 00:59:23,240
That was so fun.

1182
00:59:23,320 --> 00:59:24,480
There was zero stress.

1183
00:59:24,560 --> 00:59:27,240
Friends, we were born to be happy.

1184
00:59:27,320 --> 00:59:31,280
So, enjoying every single moment
of every day is essential.

1185
00:59:31,360 --> 00:59:33,120
Loving yourself is what matters.

1186
00:59:33,200 --> 00:59:34,800
I liked the energy.

1187
00:59:34,880 --> 00:59:36,480
I liked the dancing.

1188
00:59:36,560 --> 00:59:37,720
It didn't look awkward.

1189
00:59:37,800 --> 00:59:39,520
Hey, it was fun.

1190
00:59:39,600 --> 00:59:42,960
It felt like Broadway.
Like watching a stage play.

1191
00:59:43,640 --> 00:59:46,720
I was surprised
by Peem and Manyoo's look and energy.

1192
00:59:46,800 --> 00:59:49,360
And they created it
without me saying a word.

1193
00:59:49,440 --> 00:59:50,880
I'm lucky. I have to thank them.

1194
00:59:52,920 --> 00:59:55,120
The main part
was a pure fashion show runway.

1195
00:59:55,200 --> 00:59:58,600
I really loved it.
Everyone hit their mark perfectly.

1196
00:59:58,680 --> 01:00:01,640
Mile's team is looking like
the frontrunner.

1197
01:00:01,720 --> 01:00:03,760
Their looks are very strong.

1198
01:00:03,840 --> 01:00:05,880
Some of them
we're seeing for the first time.

1199
01:00:05,960 --> 01:00:07,440
Gluf is Mile's weak link.

1200
01:00:08,200 --> 01:00:09,840
He still has a lot to learn.

1201
01:00:09,920 --> 01:00:12,920
I'm not sure about the result,
but I did my best and had fun.

1202
01:00:14,600 --> 01:00:17,760
Gluf is very mature for a 16-year-old.

1203
01:00:17,840 --> 01:00:22,560
He's from the new generation,
but he's genuinely respectful.

1204
01:00:22,640 --> 01:00:27,600
He listens, understands, and answers
honestly from his heart. That's important.

1205
01:00:28,440 --> 01:00:29,800
There was some dead air, huh.

1206
01:00:29,880 --> 01:00:31,320
Yes, a lot.

1207
01:00:31,400 --> 01:00:32,760
I'm very confident in my team.

1208
01:00:32,840 --> 01:00:35,640
It's up to the judges now
to decide who wins.

1209
01:00:35,720 --> 01:00:38,480
I hope once Moo sees my walk,

1210
01:00:38,560 --> 01:00:42,200
he might let me walk
in an Asava fashion show.

1211
01:00:42,280 --> 01:00:45,000
His final pose is great. I like it.

1212
01:00:45,080 --> 01:00:45,960
To each their own.

1213
01:00:46,040 --> 01:00:51,080
Personally, the message about love
was practically perfect.

1214
01:00:51,160 --> 01:00:52,080
Okay.

1215
01:00:52,160 --> 01:00:54,000
If they win, we'll know…

1216
01:00:54,080 --> 01:00:55,760
- what they expect.
- Yes.

1217
01:00:55,840 --> 01:00:59,040
If it's so abstract,
you have to explain it.

1218
01:00:59,120 --> 01:01:00,920
Eventually, people won't get it.

1219
01:01:01,000 --> 01:01:02,440
It's too deep.

1220
01:01:02,520 --> 01:01:03,720
Way too deep.

1221
01:01:03,800 --> 01:01:06,000
- They went in opposite directions.
- Yes.

1222
01:01:06,080 --> 01:01:09,880
It's up to the judges now
to see which style they prefer.

1223
01:01:09,960 --> 01:01:11,800
Were they focusing mainly on the walk?

1224
01:01:11,880 --> 01:01:14,560
Did we go wrong with our creativity?

1225
01:01:14,640 --> 01:01:18,920
Judges, we've just seen the presentations
from all three teams.

1226
01:01:19,000 --> 01:01:25,600
Now, let's watch the finale show
for The Creative Cloud Canvas campaign.

1227
01:01:37,640 --> 01:01:43,120
The finale felt like a real fashion show.
Like we were really modeling the clothes.

1228
01:01:43,640 --> 01:01:47,120
I felt like a professional model.
It was so cool.

1229
01:01:56,200 --> 01:01:58,160
The lighting right here is gorgeous.

1230
01:02:02,080 --> 01:02:03,560
Damn it, Leo is so handsome.

1231
01:02:04,080 --> 01:02:05,880
Very handsome. He's a dark horse.

1232
01:02:05,960 --> 01:02:08,040
He's no dark horse anymore.

1233
01:02:08,120 --> 01:02:11,240
- He's the front-runner.
- Everyone agrees he's handsome.

1234
01:02:28,200 --> 01:02:30,440
Mew is being too much. See?

1235
01:02:30,520 --> 01:02:31,920
Yes. I see.

1236
01:02:32,000 --> 01:02:33,960
That was his best shot.

1237
01:02:34,480 --> 01:02:36,520
The energy was so high today.

1238
01:02:36,600 --> 01:02:39,440
I feel like I did better here
than in the master class.

1239
01:02:39,520 --> 01:02:41,600
Better than practice. Way better.

1240
01:02:41,680 --> 01:02:43,040
I'm happy.

1241
01:02:48,160 --> 01:02:51,560
Wow, the finale on the stairs.

1242
01:02:51,640 --> 01:02:55,240
Four girls, elegant in brick-hued dresses.

1243
01:02:55,320 --> 01:02:59,760
The finale had great color coordination.
I liked it.

1244
01:02:59,840 --> 01:03:02,560
The people on the scaffolding
were already color-coded.

1245
01:03:02,640 --> 01:03:04,240
They were perfectly on mark.

1246
01:03:04,320 --> 01:03:05,560
Everything was seamless.

1247
01:03:08,280 --> 01:03:11,000
Kim is okay. He keeps getting better.

1248
01:03:11,520 --> 01:03:14,880
- To me, Kim is the most intimidating.
- He keeps getting better.

1249
01:03:14,960 --> 01:03:15,960
He's like…

1250
01:03:16,040 --> 01:03:17,840
He's always ready.

1251
01:03:17,920 --> 01:03:20,720
Kimhan was great.
He didn't disappoint anyone, I think.

1252
01:03:20,800 --> 01:03:22,600
He also stood out in the finale.

1253
01:03:22,680 --> 01:03:26,120
I had a new look today, and I felt cute.

1254
01:03:26,720 --> 01:03:30,520
- Pu, the outfit is absolutely elegant.
- Thank you.

1255
01:03:30,600 --> 01:03:33,200
They just stood out from the rest.

1256
01:03:35,960 --> 01:03:39,880
All right, that was
The Creative Cloud Canvas campaign.

1257
01:03:39,960 --> 01:03:44,040
A grand opening
for <i>The Face Men Thailand Season 4</i>.

1258
01:03:46,600 --> 01:03:48,360
Before we get to the results,

1259
01:03:48,440 --> 01:03:51,040
let's hear some comments from our judges.

1260
01:03:51,120 --> 01:03:53,680
Starting with Team Pancake and Ananda.

1261
01:03:53,760 --> 01:03:57,120
Doing a catwalk on a massive outdoor space

1262
01:03:57,200 --> 01:03:58,280
is not an easy task.

1263
01:03:58,360 --> 01:04:01,520
The three teams
had very different perspectives.

1264
01:04:01,600 --> 01:04:04,040
Like Team Ananda and Pancake,

1265
01:04:04,120 --> 01:04:06,280
they took a very high-fashion approach.

1266
01:04:06,360 --> 01:04:07,960
The choreography was crucial.

1267
01:04:08,520 --> 01:04:11,200
When the poses didn't fit the space,

1268
01:04:11,280 --> 01:04:13,920
it caused the judges to feel disconnected.

1269
01:04:14,000 --> 01:04:17,000
With each model's unique style

1270
01:04:17,080 --> 01:04:22,280
and the vast height differences,
you need to walk as a cohesive team.

1271
01:04:22,360 --> 01:04:24,520
The entire show has to survive.

1272
01:04:24,600 --> 01:04:26,200
They didn't listen to the music.

1273
01:04:26,280 --> 01:04:29,400
When they ignore the music,
their focus shifts to

1274
01:04:29,480 --> 01:04:31,560
"What should I do? What's my next move?"

1275
01:04:31,640 --> 01:04:34,240
Kimhan was the one
elevating the whole show.

1276
01:04:34,320 --> 01:04:36,960
He was the MVP of the team today.

1277
01:04:37,040 --> 01:04:39,440
One person totally lost it,
and that was Wigrom.

1278
01:04:39,520 --> 01:04:43,560
His anxiety ended up
dragging the show down.

1279
01:04:43,640 --> 01:04:45,960
But he's very open-minded
and ready to fight.

1280
01:04:46,040 --> 01:04:49,040
If we can just get him
to go with the flow, it will be fun.

1281
01:04:49,120 --> 01:04:49,960
Agree.

1282
01:04:50,040 --> 01:04:53,400
Wigrom was the least prepared.
He really just lacks experience.

1283
01:04:53,480 --> 01:04:56,560
Let's move on to Mentor Off's team.

1284
01:04:56,640 --> 01:04:59,120
- Pu?
- The choreography is fun.

1285
01:04:59,200 --> 01:05:00,320
If perfected,

1286
01:05:00,400 --> 01:05:04,400
I can easily adapt it and build upon it.

1287
01:05:04,480 --> 01:05:08,480
And you were lucky
to have someone carry the whole show.

1288
01:05:08,560 --> 01:05:13,000
In any fashion show, there are strong,
standout, and weak models.

1289
01:05:13,080 --> 01:05:16,160
But making the whole show flow
is incredibly important.

1290
01:05:16,240 --> 01:05:18,800
But I loved the energy.
Speaking as a former Mentor.

1291
01:05:18,880 --> 01:05:22,960
More importantly,
you were smart today for bringing in help.

1292
01:05:23,040 --> 01:05:26,520
He knows how to play the game.
Mentors need to know how to play it.

1293
01:05:26,600 --> 01:05:28,400
I wanted my team to learn something.

1294
01:05:28,480 --> 01:05:30,680
That's why I brought in
a professional model.

1295
01:05:30,760 --> 01:05:33,760
But some guys were doing too much,
which was a shame.

1296
01:05:33,840 --> 01:05:37,400
When the activities you gave them
went beyond just walking.

1297
01:05:37,480 --> 01:05:38,920
You have to be careful.

1298
01:05:39,000 --> 01:05:41,120
Mew, for example. His look was strong.

1299
01:05:41,200 --> 01:05:42,560
- He looked forced.
- Right.

1300
01:05:42,640 --> 01:05:43,880
He was trying too hard.

1301
01:05:43,960 --> 01:05:46,320
It made that whole section feel awkward.

1302
01:05:46,400 --> 01:05:48,640
It just so happens
you had two leading men.

1303
01:05:48,720 --> 01:05:50,840
- Rome and Pom.
- Pom.

1304
01:05:50,920 --> 01:05:54,840
They made certain moments
look extra special.

1305
01:05:54,920 --> 01:05:57,440
So that part was pretty satisfying.

1306
01:05:57,520 --> 01:05:59,520
But it's a double-edged sword.

1307
01:05:59,600 --> 01:06:02,320
Because when they stood out,
others faded away.

1308
01:06:02,400 --> 01:06:05,520
- I just asked Moo, "Where did Bonus go?"
- Yes.

1309
01:06:05,600 --> 01:06:08,160
- "Out collecting debts."
- Indeed.

1310
01:06:08,240 --> 01:06:09,480
And where did Fox go?

1311
01:06:09,560 --> 01:06:12,080
Fox and Bonus both completely disappeared.

1312
01:06:12,160 --> 01:06:13,280
We couldn't find them.

1313
01:06:13,360 --> 01:06:17,880
Honestly, I don't know
what criteria the judges use to score.

1314
01:06:17,960 --> 01:06:19,440
Do you feel the same way?

1315
01:06:19,520 --> 01:06:22,600
And finally, Mentor Mile's team.

1316
01:06:22,680 --> 01:06:23,720
- Yes.
- How was it?

1317
01:06:23,800 --> 01:06:26,840
I have to be honest,
I couldn't keep up with everyone.

1318
01:06:26,920 --> 01:06:29,600
You need to guide the audience's eyes.

1319
01:06:29,680 --> 01:06:32,880
They lack experience.
They missed their cues.

1320
01:06:32,960 --> 01:06:35,080
Which ended up creating dead air.

1321
01:06:35,160 --> 01:06:38,800
I loved the storytelling.
I really loved Peem and Gluf.

1322
01:06:38,880 --> 01:06:41,840
- It was Peem and Manyoo.
- Sorry, it's Peem and Manyoo.

1323
01:06:41,920 --> 01:06:43,800
That was spectacular.

1324
01:06:43,880 --> 01:06:47,680
I felt there was movement,
energy, and vibrancy.

1325
01:06:47,760 --> 01:06:51,080
I never thought
they would pull off being up there.

1326
01:06:51,160 --> 01:06:53,840
One title came to mind, <i>West Side Story</i>.

1327
01:06:53,920 --> 01:06:57,720
It gave that vibe,
and it was perfectly balanced.

1328
01:06:57,800 --> 01:06:59,160
I was amazed by that part.

1329
01:06:59,240 --> 01:07:01,960
The brand owners loved it.
I was over the moon.

1330
01:07:02,040 --> 01:07:05,080
I must say, Mile is here
all alone today without any help.

1331
01:07:05,160 --> 01:07:06,280
What a gentleman.

1332
01:07:06,360 --> 01:07:08,040
- I loved it.
- Thank you.

1333
01:07:08,120 --> 01:07:10,440
Your creativity
and interpretation were fresh.

1334
01:07:10,520 --> 01:07:12,120
It's exciting and interesting.

1335
01:07:12,720 --> 01:07:15,080
The movements perfectly sync
with the models.

1336
01:07:15,160 --> 01:07:16,760
But amidst all those movements,

1337
01:07:16,840 --> 01:07:19,800
there are flaws
where it feels like dead air.

1338
01:07:19,880 --> 01:07:22,480
There's a hidden story there.

1339
01:07:22,560 --> 01:07:26,200
For the first week, especially
for the inexperienced young men,

1340
01:07:26,280 --> 01:07:29,520
anxiety held them back
from fully expressing themselves.

1341
01:07:29,600 --> 01:07:31,160
Let me give you a tip.

1342
01:07:31,240 --> 01:07:33,960
We'll have similar challenges
like this again.

1343
01:07:34,040 --> 01:07:36,640
So, keep this in mind.

1344
01:07:36,720 --> 01:07:42,480
I might have been too harsh,
making them do this on the first campaign.

1345
01:07:44,000 --> 01:07:46,120
We've heard all the comments.

1346
01:07:46,720 --> 01:07:49,400
It's time for the results.

1347
01:07:49,480 --> 01:07:54,640
Royal Mom. Which team won
The Creative Cloud Canvas campaign?

1348
01:07:54,720 --> 01:07:56,640
The winning team is…

1349
01:08:05,800 --> 01:08:06,840
Team Off.

1350
01:08:06,920 --> 01:08:08,800
Yes!

1351
01:08:08,880 --> 01:08:10,160
He deserves it.

1352
01:08:10,240 --> 01:08:12,280
Congratulations to Mentor Off's team.

1353
01:08:12,360 --> 01:08:13,560
Thank you!

1354
01:08:13,640 --> 01:08:16,720
You're the winner
of The Creative Cloud Canvas campaign.

1355
01:08:19,319 --> 01:08:23,319
I understand the mentors now.
My heart was pounding.

1356
01:08:23,399 --> 01:08:27,120
I'm so glad I chose JingJing
to join us today.

1357
01:08:27,200 --> 01:08:30,000
Having a partner to brainstorm with
made the game fun.

1358
01:08:30,080 --> 01:08:31,560
That's amazing.

1359
01:08:31,640 --> 01:08:36,399
But that also means the other two teams
must send at least one member

1360
01:08:36,479 --> 01:08:38,160
to the elimination room.

1361
01:08:38,240 --> 01:08:41,359
And Mentor Off,
you must eliminate one person.

1362
01:08:41,439 --> 01:08:43,319
Two heads are better than one.

1363
01:08:43,399 --> 01:08:46,200
That proverb rings true today.

1364
01:08:46,279 --> 01:08:48,680
Mentor Mile might be new to this game.

1365
01:08:48,760 --> 01:08:51,520
You know what to do now, right?

1366
01:08:51,600 --> 01:08:54,200
- Eliminate one.
- Sure, either yours or Ananda's team.

1367
01:08:54,840 --> 01:08:55,960
Off, you want anything?

1368
01:08:56,040 --> 01:08:59,160
Pan, if there's another runway challenge,
I'll force you to join us.

1369
01:08:59,240 --> 01:09:02,359
I'll drag you here.
I won't take no for an answer.

1370
01:09:02,439 --> 01:09:05,439
For today, a big thanks to Cloud 11

1371
01:09:05,520 --> 01:09:08,439
for providing the venue
for today's challenge.

1372
01:09:08,520 --> 01:09:13,520
Also, thank you to our four judges
for joining us today.

1373
01:09:13,600 --> 01:09:14,800
Thank you.

1374
01:09:14,880 --> 01:09:16,439
I won't be able to sleep tonight.

1375
01:09:16,520 --> 01:09:21,120
Honestly, you never know
what will happen on <i>The Face</i>.

1376
01:09:21,200 --> 01:09:24,479
Those who underperformed just need
more practice. It's that simple.

1377
01:09:24,560 --> 01:09:26,399
I'm practically accepting my fate.

1378
01:09:26,479 --> 01:09:28,439
Welcome to <i>The Face Thailand</i>.

1379
01:09:28,520 --> 01:09:29,560
I get it now.

1380
01:09:41,520 --> 01:09:43,479
- Hello.
- Hello.

1381
01:09:43,560 --> 01:09:44,840
Hello.

1382
01:09:45,479 --> 01:09:48,439
When Mentor Pancake walked in,
I felt the vibe…

1383
01:09:49,319 --> 01:09:50,840
completely drop.

1384
01:09:50,920 --> 01:09:53,240
My heart sank when…

1385
01:09:53,880 --> 01:09:55,320
Pancake walked in.

1386
01:09:55,400 --> 01:09:56,680
You look serious.

1387
01:09:56,760 --> 01:09:59,560
- Not just my bold makeup.
- I meant your mood.

1388
01:09:59,640 --> 01:10:01,240
Right. My mood too.

1389
01:10:01,320 --> 01:10:03,000
The result is…

1390
01:10:03,600 --> 01:10:04,640
we lost.

1391
01:10:04,720 --> 01:10:06,480
For several reasons.

1392
01:10:06,560 --> 01:10:10,000
Based on the judges' feedback
and personal preferences.

1393
01:10:10,080 --> 01:10:11,120
It's quite stressful.

1394
01:10:11,200 --> 01:10:15,280
I don't know who she'll send
to the Black Room.

1395
01:10:15,360 --> 01:10:17,400
Let's video call Ananda.

1396
01:10:17,480 --> 01:10:20,600
You need to hear
what Ananda and I will discuss,

1397
01:10:20,680 --> 01:10:23,680
and decide who will be sent
to the Black Room.

1398
01:10:23,760 --> 01:10:27,040
Who has to fight for their spot to return?

1399
01:10:28,760 --> 01:10:29,720
Hey.

1400
01:10:29,800 --> 01:10:32,760
- Yes!
- What's up?

1401
01:10:32,840 --> 01:10:34,160
Hello.

1402
01:10:34,240 --> 01:10:36,880
When Mile walked in,
I was waiting to hear one thing,

1403
01:10:36,960 --> 01:10:38,040
"We won."

1404
01:10:38,120 --> 01:10:39,640
- You want to know the result?
- Yes.

1405
01:10:39,720 --> 01:10:41,480
Do you think we won or lost?

1406
01:10:41,560 --> 01:10:45,440
We were just talking,
and we're fairly confident that…

1407
01:10:45,520 --> 01:10:47,840
We have a chance. At least we…

1408
01:10:47,920 --> 01:10:50,280
stand a chance of winning.
We definitely do.

1409
01:10:51,600 --> 01:10:53,120
All right, I'll announce it.

1410
01:10:56,400 --> 01:10:57,600
Team Off won.

1411
01:10:59,320 --> 01:11:01,760
When Mile had to pick someone
for the Black Room,

1412
01:11:01,840 --> 01:11:03,480
I went completely pale.

1413
01:11:03,560 --> 01:11:05,840
He was staring right at me.

1414
01:11:05,920 --> 01:11:07,880
I'm definitely going to the Black Room.

1415
01:11:11,080 --> 01:11:12,280
There he is.

1416
01:11:15,160 --> 01:11:16,240
I knew it.

1417
01:11:16,840 --> 01:11:19,400
They all did well in the last round.

1418
01:11:19,480 --> 01:11:22,040
But you should know

1419
01:11:22,120 --> 01:11:24,440
that some of you still have weak points.

1420
01:11:24,520 --> 01:11:29,160
Do you think you did your best
in the last campaign?

1421
01:11:29,240 --> 01:11:30,800
- 100%.
- Really? 100%?

1422
01:11:30,880 --> 01:11:32,400
- 120%.
- 130%.

1423
01:11:32,480 --> 01:11:33,480
130%.

1424
01:11:33,560 --> 01:11:35,240
- 90%.
- You look stressed.

1425
01:11:35,800 --> 01:11:36,880
I gave it my all.

1426
01:11:36,960 --> 01:11:41,440
Everyone praised Rome and Pom
for a great opening.

1427
01:11:41,520 --> 01:11:42,840
Everything was perfect.

1428
01:11:42,920 --> 01:11:44,280
That leaves three of you.

1429
01:11:44,360 --> 01:11:45,680
Fox,

1430
01:11:45,760 --> 01:11:47,440
Bonus, and Mew.

1431
01:11:47,520 --> 01:11:49,680
Man, our team was so stressed out.

1432
01:11:49,760 --> 01:11:52,040
I heard the cheering screams.

1433
01:11:52,800 --> 01:11:55,640
So I knew my team was screwed.

1434
01:11:55,720 --> 01:11:57,040
Someone was going home.

1435
01:11:57,120 --> 01:12:00,880
Tell me the biggest mistake
you made that day.

1436
01:12:00,960 --> 01:12:03,080
Explain what happened.

1437
01:12:03,160 --> 01:12:05,320
I posed too much.

1438
01:12:05,400 --> 01:12:07,480
And it got repetitive.

1439
01:12:08,280 --> 01:12:12,440
I was stressed.
I knew I didn't do my best.

1440
01:12:12,520 --> 01:12:15,720
Honestly, I didn't give
my 100% when posing.

1441
01:12:15,800 --> 01:12:19,840
I just moved slightly,
thinking people wouldn't notice.

1442
01:12:19,920 --> 01:12:22,400
But I can't do that.
I have to give it my all.

1443
01:12:22,480 --> 01:12:25,800
I learned my lesson.
If I do it, I have to go all out.

1444
01:12:25,880 --> 01:12:28,280
- You have to be completely confident.
- Noted.

1445
01:12:28,360 --> 01:12:30,960
I get it. My confidence was just gone.

1446
01:12:31,040 --> 01:12:33,240
That day, I felt that

1447
01:12:33,320 --> 01:12:39,360
I didn't have as much energy as I wanted.

1448
01:12:39,440 --> 01:12:41,440
- You knew it, right?
- I knew it.

1449
01:12:41,520 --> 01:12:44,560
I need more focus and confidence.

1450
01:12:44,640 --> 01:12:46,200
I should have more confidence.

1451
01:12:46,280 --> 01:12:48,800
The three people I'm picking

1452
01:12:50,040 --> 01:12:52,000
are Fox, Mew,

1453
01:12:52,600 --> 01:12:53,680
and Bonus.

1454
01:12:53,760 --> 01:12:56,360
Three people?
That leaves only two on the team?

1455
01:12:57,920 --> 01:12:59,440
Everyone turned pale.

1456
01:12:59,520 --> 01:13:01,520
You don't have to go because we won.

1457
01:13:06,560 --> 01:13:09,280
I'm super happy. I'm thrilled.

1458
01:13:09,360 --> 01:13:12,640
What? We won again!

1459
01:13:12,720 --> 01:13:14,240
I'm exhausted.

1460
01:13:15,760 --> 01:13:18,080
I'm more stressed than you guys.

1461
01:13:18,160 --> 01:13:20,520
Honestly, I couldn't tell you.

1462
01:13:21,560 --> 01:13:22,560
Oh, brother.

1463
01:13:22,640 --> 01:13:23,720
Stressed?

1464
01:13:24,720 --> 01:13:27,720
Hey, don't cry. Why are you crying?

1465
01:13:27,800 --> 01:13:30,000
I think I revealed it too soon.

1466
01:13:30,080 --> 01:13:32,160
I shouldn't have done that.

1467
01:13:32,240 --> 01:13:34,440
Because Mew was tearing up too.

1468
01:13:34,520 --> 01:13:37,680
When I mentioned the Black Room,
he started tearing up.

1469
01:13:38,880 --> 01:13:43,040
<i>First of all, I'm proud of everyone.</i>

1470
01:13:45,160 --> 01:13:47,240
<i>It's a perfect example</i>

1471
01:13:47,320 --> 01:13:51,200
<i>of how to make the most of an opportunity.</i>

1472
01:13:51,280 --> 01:13:53,520
<i>I'm not ready to let anyone go.</i>

1473
01:13:53,600 --> 01:13:55,960
<i>I still want to get to know all of you.</i>

1474
01:13:56,040 --> 01:13:59,480
<i>I feel like everyone has more potential.</i>

1475
01:13:59,560 --> 01:14:02,200
Everyone is highly talented, but…

1476
01:14:02,280 --> 01:14:05,200
I hope I'm not the worst.

1477
01:14:05,280 --> 01:14:06,840
<i>And I felt…</i>

1478
01:14:09,840 --> 01:14:13,720
<i>It feels unfair</i>
<i>to eliminate someone this early.</i>

1479
01:14:13,800 --> 01:14:15,160
<i>But for this week,</i>

1480
01:14:17,160 --> 01:14:18,480
<i>I choose…</i>

1481
01:14:20,800 --> 01:14:22,240
<i>Wigrom.</i>

1482
01:14:25,240 --> 01:14:27,800
I understand that I might be the weakest.

1483
01:14:27,880 --> 01:14:31,400
My team is full of talented people.
Everyone has experience.

1484
01:14:31,480 --> 01:14:33,120
I'm the youngest.

1485
01:14:33,200 --> 01:14:35,040
- Wigrom, are you ready?
- Yes, I'm ready.

1486
01:14:35,120 --> 01:14:38,160
Don't be afraid. Take a deep breath.

1487
01:14:38,240 --> 01:14:41,840
I'm not sending you in
because you're the youngest or the worst.

1488
01:14:42,520 --> 01:14:44,080
That's only part of it.

1489
01:14:44,160 --> 01:14:46,040
But I believe you're a fighter.

1490
01:14:46,120 --> 01:14:48,120
You can achieve anything you want.

1491
01:14:48,200 --> 01:14:51,280
Whether it's asking for a chance
or proving yourself.

1492
01:14:51,880 --> 01:14:53,120
Talk to him.

1493
01:14:54,040 --> 01:14:56,480
And I believe Mentor Off

1494
01:14:56,560 --> 01:14:58,200
will send you back.

1495
01:14:59,560 --> 01:15:00,880
He'll be back.

1496
01:15:01,400 --> 01:15:05,200
I'm confident
that Wigrom will put up a fight.

1497
01:15:05,280 --> 01:15:06,720
And he'll succeed.

1498
01:15:07,840 --> 01:15:10,800
Since we didn't win, someone has to go.

1499
01:15:14,880 --> 01:15:17,520
Any volunteers?

1500
01:15:23,520 --> 01:15:26,160
Someone has to go.

1501
01:15:26,240 --> 01:15:28,160
No one wants to go.

1502
01:15:28,240 --> 01:15:32,160
I don't want anyone on my team
in the Black Room.

1503
01:15:32,240 --> 01:15:34,120
I have to make a choice.

1504
01:15:34,200 --> 01:15:36,560
This is a really tough decision.

1505
01:15:36,640 --> 01:15:39,480
I couldn't sleep for the first few nights.

1506
01:15:39,560 --> 01:15:41,480
I kept wondering what to do.

1507
01:15:41,560 --> 01:15:44,600
Listen carefully.
I'm sending you to fight.

1508
01:15:44,680 --> 01:15:47,400
So I'll pick someone who…

1509
01:15:48,000 --> 01:15:50,320
has a fighting spirit.

1510
01:15:51,040 --> 01:15:54,960
I see that in him.
I think he can handle this.

1511
01:15:55,960 --> 01:15:57,240
Are you ready?

1512
01:15:59,000 --> 01:16:01,600
Hey, remember to breathe.
Don't hold your breath.

1513
01:16:05,080 --> 01:16:08,040
Gluf, can you fight if I send you in?

1514
01:16:08,120 --> 01:16:09,080
I'll try my best.

1515
01:16:09,160 --> 01:16:11,280
I was completely numb. I was speechless.

1516
01:16:11,360 --> 01:16:14,960
Before and after it happened.

1517
01:16:15,040 --> 01:16:18,000
I think the others
are highly skilled. And…

1518
01:16:18,080 --> 01:16:21,040
even though I lack experience,

1519
01:16:21,920 --> 01:16:25,280
I have a fighter's spirit.

1520
01:16:26,080 --> 01:16:30,600
Honestly,
I think I can win Mentor Off over.

1521
01:16:30,680 --> 01:16:32,120
You're a cat with nine lives.

1522
01:16:32,200 --> 01:16:33,440
Tawanchai never dies.

1523
01:16:33,520 --> 01:16:35,080
Yes.

1524
01:16:35,640 --> 01:16:37,520
One, two, three.

1525
01:16:37,600 --> 01:16:38,880
- Go Team Mile!
- Go Team Mile!

1526
01:16:39,920 --> 01:16:41,720
It might not be the best play,

1527
01:16:42,920 --> 01:16:44,560
but I think it's…

1528
01:16:44,640 --> 01:16:49,240
the most appropriate strategy
for this round.

1529
01:17:10,280 --> 01:17:11,400
Hello.

1530
01:17:11,480 --> 01:17:12,600
- Hello.
- Hello.

1531
01:17:12,680 --> 01:17:14,040
Well…

1532
01:17:14,120 --> 01:17:17,360
First, I have to thank both mentors

1533
01:17:17,440 --> 01:17:21,120
for actually sending
their weakest members.

1534
01:17:21,840 --> 01:17:24,520
What are your weaknesses?
Why did they send you here?

1535
01:17:24,600 --> 01:17:27,480
To the judges, I seemed

1536
01:17:27,560 --> 01:17:30,400
a bit absent-minded.

1537
01:17:30,480 --> 01:17:33,360
Shifty-eyed and anxious.

1538
01:17:33,440 --> 01:17:35,200
And awkward.

1539
01:17:35,280 --> 01:17:37,520
I think I still lack experience.

1540
01:17:37,600 --> 01:17:41,760
I haven't been through enough.
I just don't have enough experience.

1541
01:17:43,640 --> 01:17:48,160
The mentors probably already know
who belongs in the Final Walk.

1542
01:17:48,240 --> 01:17:50,400
Maybe they just
don't picture you two there.

1543
01:17:50,480 --> 01:17:52,760
Mentor Mile said he chose me

1544
01:17:52,840 --> 01:17:55,680
because he believes
I can fight my way back.

1545
01:17:55,760 --> 01:17:59,400
- Did they tell you their reason?
- They chose me so I would fight.

1546
01:17:59,480 --> 01:18:03,160
They believe I can make it back.

1547
01:18:03,240 --> 01:18:05,200
Really? So the game is on then.

1548
01:18:06,200 --> 01:18:09,880
Mentors sent in the members
who are likely to make it.

1549
01:18:09,960 --> 01:18:11,320
That's what Mile told me.

1550
01:18:11,400 --> 01:18:13,400
- And do you believe him?
- I do.

1551
01:18:13,480 --> 01:18:15,800
I can do it. I can fight.

1552
01:18:15,880 --> 01:18:17,840
If he believed in you, why send you here?

1553
01:18:17,920 --> 01:18:20,200
- Shouldn't it be someone else?
- I believe Mile.

1554
01:18:20,280 --> 01:18:22,800
- Oh, you do?
- Yes, he's my mentor.

1555
01:18:22,880 --> 01:18:25,840
Okay. And you believe Pan too.

1556
01:18:25,920 --> 01:18:29,360
I was eliminated once before
for the same reason.

1557
01:18:29,440 --> 01:18:31,880
When I found out I had a second chance,

1558
01:18:31,960 --> 01:18:35,280
I used that time to improve.
I did everything to get better.

1559
01:18:35,360 --> 01:18:39,320
And I showed everyone that I've improved.

1560
01:18:39,400 --> 01:18:41,000
Since coming to <i>The Face</i>,

1561
01:18:41,080 --> 01:18:44,240
I got the chance to show off
and improve myself.

1562
01:18:44,320 --> 01:18:45,520
"Show off"?

1563
01:18:45,600 --> 01:18:46,880
I'm sorry. I…

1564
01:18:46,960 --> 01:18:50,760
I got the chance to improve myself.

1565
01:18:50,840 --> 01:18:53,000
Do you think your improvement is enough?

1566
01:18:53,080 --> 01:18:54,680
I believe I can grow even more.

1567
01:18:54,760 --> 01:18:57,200
My whole life is
about constant self-improvement.

1568
01:18:57,280 --> 01:19:00,640
He says he can still improve,
but so can I.

1569
01:19:00,720 --> 01:19:03,600
I also believe I can keep improving.

1570
01:19:03,680 --> 01:19:07,760
If I get to stay, I believe I would learn
many things from <i>The Face</i>.

1571
01:19:07,840 --> 01:19:11,200
So that I could become the man
<i>The Face Men </i>is looking for.

1572
01:19:11,280 --> 01:19:13,000
But this is Season 4.

1573
01:19:13,080 --> 01:19:16,200
Before applying, shouldn't you have known
you needed to be ready?

1574
01:19:16,280 --> 01:19:19,080
How do you think
you can compete with the others?

1575
01:19:19,160 --> 01:19:21,400
You can't. It's too exhausting.

1576
01:19:22,000 --> 01:19:26,800
I feel like there's still a lot
the mentors haven't seen.

1577
01:19:26,880 --> 01:19:30,360
I have a strong sense of self,
yet I am adaptable.

1578
01:19:30,440 --> 01:19:34,080
I'm flexible and can handle any situation.

1579
01:19:34,160 --> 01:19:37,200
There's a lot I still lack
in the entertainment industry.

1580
01:19:37,280 --> 01:19:39,880
I want to learn from <i>The Face</i>.

1581
01:19:39,960 --> 01:19:42,640
I just started here in <i>The Face</i>.

1582
01:19:42,720 --> 01:19:45,320
But it feels like I've been
in the industry for ages.

1583
01:19:45,400 --> 01:19:50,440
I believe my personality and Gen Z nature

1584
01:19:50,520 --> 01:19:53,880
can show people what I'm capable of.

1585
01:19:53,960 --> 01:19:55,960
I think you're a bit
too confident, Wigrom.

1586
01:19:56,040 --> 01:19:58,960
Being overly confident
doesn't really do you any favors.

1587
01:19:59,040 --> 01:20:03,080
I see it in everything,
like how you speak to the crew.

1588
01:20:03,160 --> 01:20:04,840
You might need to tone it down.

1589
01:20:04,920 --> 01:20:09,600
I apologize for that.
I promise to improve.

1590
01:20:09,680 --> 01:20:13,040
If I'm eliminated,
I won't have any regrets.

1591
01:20:13,120 --> 01:20:14,960
Because I feel I've done my best.

1592
01:20:19,960 --> 01:20:22,960
I'll keep pursuing my goals.

1593
01:20:23,040 --> 01:20:25,440
From what he's said,
I think I can do that too.

1594
01:20:25,520 --> 01:20:29,040
I really understand Gen Z,
if given the chance.

1595
01:20:29,120 --> 01:20:33,000
Gluf, I've seen you
since the very first team selection.

1596
01:20:33,080 --> 01:20:34,640
You looked like a real fighter.

1597
01:20:34,720 --> 01:20:37,320
Honestly, I want both of you to stay.

1598
01:20:37,400 --> 01:20:40,400
Because that benefits my team.

1599
01:20:40,480 --> 01:20:42,080
Then let me stay.

1600
01:20:42,160 --> 01:20:44,080
I have to eliminate one person.

1601
01:20:44,160 --> 01:20:47,720
I'm just making the decision
after your mentors did.

1602
01:20:51,280 --> 01:20:53,200
These two kids are inexperienced.

1603
01:20:53,280 --> 01:20:57,040
And they're both contestants
that their mentors didn't even pick.

1604
01:20:57,120 --> 01:21:00,760
If I eliminate them, deep down,
their mentors will be glad.

1605
01:21:04,560 --> 01:21:06,480
I was anxious. Off walked out first.

1606
01:21:06,560 --> 01:21:09,520
He didn't chat with anyone.
Went straight to Mile.

1607
01:21:09,600 --> 01:21:12,560
Mile, what you said earlier…

1608
01:21:12,640 --> 01:21:15,400
I just feel like
you shouldn't have done that.

1609
01:21:15,480 --> 01:21:18,840
The rules never stated whether
I could or could not bring any help.

1610
01:21:18,920 --> 01:21:21,960
I brought in JingJing to help my team win.

1611
01:21:22,040 --> 01:21:25,560
What? What's going on with these two?

1612
01:21:25,640 --> 01:21:26,880
It felt weird.

1613
01:21:26,960 --> 01:21:29,760
When Off walked over to Mentor Mile,
I was shocked.

1614
01:21:29,840 --> 01:21:33,840
I had no idea what they were discussing
when they met earlier.

1615
01:21:34,440 --> 01:21:35,800
What's up?

1616
01:21:35,880 --> 01:21:37,040
No, I just…

1617
01:21:37,120 --> 01:21:40,600
When you had your helper coach your team,

1618
01:21:40,680 --> 01:21:42,640
I just felt it was a bit unfair.

1619
01:21:42,720 --> 01:21:44,960
I don't want to send anyone
to the Black Room.

1620
01:21:45,600 --> 01:21:49,360
But the rules already state
you must send at least one person.

1621
01:21:49,440 --> 01:21:51,600
- Let's talk to Tae.
- Okay.

1622
01:21:52,120 --> 01:21:55,080
I must speak up
because it doesn't just affect my team.

1623
01:21:55,160 --> 01:21:57,280
Is there anything I should know?

1624
01:21:57,360 --> 01:21:59,840
- Yes, Pan.
- Oh, hello.

1625
01:21:59,920 --> 01:22:01,920
- On the competition day…
- Yes.

1626
01:22:02,000 --> 01:22:03,880
- Just for this campaign.
- Okay.

1627
01:22:03,960 --> 01:22:06,320
I feel it's unfair to the contestants.

1628
01:22:06,400 --> 01:22:09,360
Secondly, I didn't know we could do that.

1629
01:22:09,440 --> 01:22:13,040
Mile thinks it was unfair
when he did the campaign by himself.

1630
01:22:13,120 --> 01:22:15,520
Mentor Off had someone helping him.

1631
01:22:15,600 --> 01:22:19,200
If I wanted to do that, I could.
I have already asked the producers.

1632
01:22:19,280 --> 01:22:20,720
Okay, I get it's a game.

1633
01:22:21,320 --> 01:22:25,080
But sending someone
just to be eliminated isn't fair.

1634
01:22:25,160 --> 01:22:27,080
He feels disadvantaged.

1635
01:22:27,160 --> 01:22:31,400
And it affects everyone on our show.

1636
01:22:31,480 --> 01:22:33,760
Why did it turn out to be my fault?

1637
01:22:33,840 --> 01:22:38,480
It might not be wrong to someone,
but to many others, it is.

1638
01:22:38,560 --> 01:22:40,920
Mile, you should have
discussed this earlier.

1639
01:22:41,000 --> 01:22:43,560
Bringing it up today doesn't fix anything.

1640
01:22:43,640 --> 01:22:46,600
It's up to you,
but I must respect the Black Room winner.

1641
01:22:46,680 --> 01:22:49,120
Someone has to go either way.

1642
01:22:49,200 --> 01:22:52,680
Once the judges have decided,
we must respect their decision.

1643
01:22:52,760 --> 01:22:54,520
Right. Then send someone in.

1644
01:22:55,440 --> 01:22:56,360
I understand.

1645
01:22:56,440 --> 01:22:59,280
If you want to balance fairness,

1646
01:22:59,360 --> 01:23:02,120
you should eliminate the weakest
based on performance.

1647
01:23:02,200 --> 01:23:03,440
- Don't worry.
- That's all.

1648
01:23:03,520 --> 01:23:06,000
Our show needs stricter rules…

1649
01:23:07,240 --> 01:23:09,320
- Much stricter.
- Definitely stricter.

1650
01:23:09,400 --> 01:23:12,880
I understand, but why bring it up now?
It feels like you disrespected me.

1651
01:23:12,960 --> 01:23:15,960
I was pretty annoyed
because I did my homework.

1652
01:23:16,040 --> 01:23:19,040
I wanted to do well
and have it turn out okay.

1653
01:23:19,120 --> 01:23:21,640
You need to watch more
of the previous seasons.

1654
01:23:21,720 --> 01:23:24,680
Ask Pan how she prepares.

1655
01:23:24,760 --> 01:23:29,160
I didn't plan to do things
the way <i>The Face </i>used to.

1656
01:23:29,240 --> 01:23:33,160
I came here to bring
my own style to <i>The Face</i>.

1657
01:23:33,680 --> 01:23:35,760
Otherwise,
you'll be begging every episode.

1658
01:23:35,840 --> 01:23:37,520
That just won't work.

1659
01:23:37,600 --> 01:23:39,200
I get it, but here's the thing.

1660
01:23:39,280 --> 01:23:42,040
I wasn't begging. That's not what I meant.

1661
01:23:42,120 --> 01:23:46,360
I spoke up because I didn't want
my supporters watching the show,

1662
01:23:46,440 --> 01:23:49,640
or anyone else watching,
to think it's okay to exploit loopholes.

1663
01:23:49,720 --> 01:23:52,840
Loopholes in the methods
that let you take advantage of others.

1664
01:23:54,080 --> 01:23:57,760
Things are the way they are
because we keep cutting corners.

1665
01:23:57,840 --> 01:24:01,520
Mile, you know that on this show,
people want to win.

1666
01:24:01,600 --> 01:24:05,160
It can start with us.
It really starts with small things.

1667
01:24:05,240 --> 01:24:08,000
I didn't mean that you cheated. No.

1668
01:24:08,080 --> 01:24:10,080
It was such a cute scene.

1669
01:24:10,160 --> 01:24:11,120
Cute argument.

1670
01:24:11,200 --> 01:24:13,200
It feels like a TV drama.

1671
01:24:15,920 --> 01:24:18,400
The vibe was so tense.

1672
01:24:18,480 --> 01:24:20,760
I just want to know
whether Wigrom made it or not.

1673
01:24:20,840 --> 01:24:23,800
Fight for him. Where is our boy?

1674
01:24:23,880 --> 01:24:26,320
I really want to keep watching, but…

1675
01:24:26,400 --> 01:24:28,960
I want to know
whose contestant gets to stay.

1676
01:24:29,840 --> 01:24:31,240
I'll bring him back to you.

1677
01:24:31,320 --> 01:24:32,680
Off walked back there.

1678
01:24:32,760 --> 01:24:36,760
Then we had to wait and see
if Wigrom would return to the team.

1679
01:24:36,840 --> 01:24:39,640
At that moment, I just hoped
Wigrom would come back.

1680
01:24:39,720 --> 01:24:42,520
If he wants to play the good guy,
he has to save both of them.

1681
01:24:43,560 --> 01:24:47,120
For the one who doesn't advance,
I have to return the portfolio, right?

1682
01:24:49,360 --> 01:24:50,440
Therefore…

1683
01:24:58,080 --> 01:24:59,760
You are not The Face.

1684
01:25:00,640 --> 01:25:02,600
I fight my own way.

1685
01:25:02,680 --> 01:25:05,120
Everything I said came from my own words.

1686
01:25:05,200 --> 01:25:08,080
Gluf took a lot of what I said.

1687
01:25:08,160 --> 01:25:10,800
He merely repeated my points.

1688
01:25:10,880 --> 01:25:12,960
I felt it was never really fair.

1689
01:25:13,040 --> 01:25:17,520
Or maybe he was just afraid
I would be a threat to his team.

1690
01:25:17,600 --> 01:25:20,600
So he chose to eliminate
the tough competitor first.

1691
01:25:20,680 --> 01:25:21,920
I understand that.

1692
01:25:31,840 --> 01:25:34,400
I couldn't explain it then,
but I was angry.

1693
01:25:34,480 --> 01:25:36,320
I felt angry, which is fine.

1694
01:25:36,400 --> 01:25:38,920
My boy came back, so I'm relieved.

1695
01:25:39,000 --> 01:25:42,080
If you two just argued
and ended up eliminating Wigrom,

1696
01:25:42,160 --> 01:25:43,880
that's ridiculous.

1697
01:25:43,960 --> 01:25:48,360
At first, I secretly hoped he would return
since Mentor Off said,

1698
01:25:48,440 --> 01:25:49,480
"I'll bring him back."

1699
01:25:49,560 --> 01:25:50,880
I'm sad and disappointed.

1700
01:25:50,960 --> 01:25:53,200
I wish I had the chance
to know Wigrom better.

1701
01:25:53,280 --> 01:25:55,160
He has many sides we haven't seen yet.

1702
01:25:55,240 --> 01:25:58,280
Wasn't he the contestant
you didn't pick from the start?

1703
01:25:58,360 --> 01:26:02,040
Whether I picked him or not,
he's on my team, so he is my team.

1704
01:26:02,120 --> 01:26:04,440
It doesn't matter
whether I chose him or not.

1705
01:26:04,520 --> 01:26:05,680
But I'm the winner.

1706
01:26:05,760 --> 01:26:08,640
Honestly? You're probably glad
I helped eliminate him.

1707
01:26:08,720 --> 01:26:11,320
He's my kid now.
There's no doubt about it.

1708
01:26:11,400 --> 01:26:14,280
He's 100% on my team.

1709
01:26:14,360 --> 01:26:16,120
Wow, that moment was terrifying.

1710
01:26:16,200 --> 01:26:17,840
I didn't know what Pan was thinking.

1711
01:26:17,920 --> 01:26:19,600
I didn't know what Off was thinking.

1712
01:26:19,680 --> 01:26:22,240
There were two choices. And I chose one.

1713
01:26:22,320 --> 01:26:24,400
- How did he fight?
- He spoke better.

1714
01:26:24,480 --> 01:26:27,720
Wigrom said he came to show off.
That's useless.

1715
01:26:27,800 --> 01:26:30,080
Go elsewhere. Don't do it here.

1716
01:26:30,160 --> 01:26:32,640
That's one of the reasons
I didn't keep Wigrom.

1717
01:26:32,720 --> 01:26:34,080
Did he really say that?

1718
01:26:34,160 --> 01:26:35,960
Do I even need to tell you?

1719
01:26:36,040 --> 01:26:38,640
Shouldn't I know? You eliminated my guy.

1720
01:26:38,720 --> 01:26:42,680
I'm pretty sure Wigrom
at least tried to fight.

1721
01:26:42,760 --> 01:26:44,480
That's not necessary for me.

1722
01:26:44,560 --> 01:26:46,640
My job is to eliminate, not to explain.

1723
01:26:46,720 --> 01:26:49,480
Do I have to explain myself to her?
Is it in the rules?

1724
01:26:49,560 --> 01:26:52,520
Of course, I need to know.
You sent my guy home.

1725
01:26:52,600 --> 01:26:56,080
Does the winner have to sit and explain?
Not at all.

1726
01:26:56,160 --> 01:26:57,520
There was no explanation.

1727
01:26:57,600 --> 01:26:59,240
Okay, fine.

1728
01:26:59,320 --> 01:27:01,680
Then I won't explain
when I eliminate someone either.

1729
01:27:01,760 --> 01:27:03,360
Sure. Just win first.

1730
01:27:03,440 --> 01:27:06,800
I'll just cut. My word is final.
No questions.

1731
01:27:06,880 --> 01:27:07,880
No explanations.

1732
01:27:07,960 --> 01:27:10,040
Oh, crap. I'm screwed.

1733
01:27:11,240 --> 01:27:12,560
Are you happy?

1734
01:27:12,640 --> 01:27:15,440
No, I'm not. I told you I talked to Off.

1735
01:27:15,520 --> 01:27:17,880
I'm not saying Off was fair or unfair.

1736
01:27:17,960 --> 01:27:21,120
I just talked to find a middle ground
for him to decide.

1737
01:27:21,200 --> 01:27:25,000
I get that Pancake
has probably been through a lot too.

1738
01:27:25,080 --> 01:27:28,280
Probably more than I can imagine.

1739
01:27:28,360 --> 01:27:32,200
Is it because Mile asked
about rules we weren't aware of,

1740
01:27:32,280 --> 01:27:34,080
so you helped his team instead?

1741
01:27:34,160 --> 01:27:36,560
- That is not it.
- Is there something I don't know?

1742
01:27:36,640 --> 01:27:38,480
No. I'm being honest with you.

1743
01:27:38,560 --> 01:27:41,880
- I don't make deals to save my team.
- I don't know.

1744
01:27:41,960 --> 01:27:45,480
A game is a game.
I just have to play along.

1745
01:27:45,560 --> 01:27:48,240
Making demands when a decision
is about to be made…

1746
01:27:48,320 --> 01:27:50,600
I think that's truly unfair.

1747
01:27:50,680 --> 01:27:53,320
It's up to you, but I'm not like that.

1748
01:27:53,400 --> 01:27:55,480
Mentor Pancake is taking a big hit.

1749
01:27:55,560 --> 01:27:57,960
Is Pancake upset? Can someone ask her?

1750
01:27:58,040 --> 01:27:59,360
Is Pancake upset?

1751
01:27:59,440 --> 01:28:02,600
Honestly, I can tell
she's acting sometimes.

1752
01:28:02,680 --> 01:28:04,880
Sometimes it's a performance, sometimes…

1753
01:28:05,880 --> 01:28:09,520
You probably didn't picture Wigrom
in the Final Walk anyway.

1754
01:28:09,600 --> 01:28:11,520
I did you a favor by eliminating him.

1755
01:28:11,600 --> 01:28:14,720
Whether you pictured him or not,
that's my business.

1756
01:28:14,800 --> 01:28:17,080
But now, he's completely
out of the picture.

1757
01:28:18,120 --> 01:28:21,160
Our mentor is so confident.
We have to win next week.

1758
01:28:21,240 --> 01:28:25,400
Confidence is fine, but don't get cocky.
I'll be 115% confident.

1759
01:28:25,480 --> 01:28:27,200
We still have to give it our all.

1760
01:28:27,280 --> 01:28:30,640
Good. My four contestants
are all top quality.

1761
01:28:30,720 --> 01:28:32,240
Hope your team won't mess up.

1762
01:28:32,320 --> 01:28:33,160
Let's go.

1763
01:28:33,240 --> 01:28:35,440
It shows she loves all of us.

1764
01:28:35,520 --> 01:28:37,720
It makes me trust her even more.

1765
01:28:37,800 --> 01:28:39,280
It means she really cares.

1766
01:28:41,720 --> 01:28:43,880
I love that word. It's so…

1767
01:28:43,960 --> 01:28:45,440
hungry and powerful.

1768
01:28:46,520 --> 01:28:48,120
Bring the heat, we'll fire back.

1769
01:28:48,200 --> 01:28:49,680
If they fight, we fight back.

1770
01:28:49,760 --> 01:28:51,120
I'm not scared either.

1771
01:28:51,840 --> 01:28:53,240
Thank you. It is what it is.

1772
01:28:53,320 --> 01:28:55,880
No, your boy really fought.
I felt it had to be Gluf.

1773
01:28:55,960 --> 01:28:58,280
I feel like Mile is more on our side now.

1774
01:28:58,360 --> 01:29:00,120
Like Mile really understands us.

1775
01:29:00,200 --> 01:29:01,280
Okay. See you.

1776
01:29:01,360 --> 01:29:03,720
All right. Enjoy the game, guys.
Enjoy the game.

1777
01:29:03,800 --> 01:29:05,120
Peace.

1778
01:29:05,200 --> 01:29:06,680
Just making peace, that's all.

1779
01:29:06,760 --> 01:29:10,760
I don't know if Mentor Off used this…

1780
01:29:10,840 --> 01:29:13,080
as a reason to save Mentor Mile's team.

1781
01:29:13,160 --> 01:29:15,800
She's probably annoyed that she lost.

1782
01:29:15,880 --> 01:29:18,800
This is how the real world works,
but not for me.

1783
01:29:18,880 --> 01:29:21,000
He's probably happy for this team.

1784
01:29:21,080 --> 01:29:23,400
It is what it is.
If you're happy, I'm happy.

1785
01:29:23,480 --> 01:29:25,200
Keep watching.

1786
01:29:27,480 --> 01:29:29,240
Is your whole team going shirtless?

1787
01:29:31,240 --> 01:29:34,040
<i>I have a shooting pain</i>
<i>radiating down my entire leg.</i>

1788
01:29:34,760 --> 01:29:38,200
For today's campaign,
we'll be shooting underwater.

1789
01:29:40,480 --> 01:29:43,560
<i>It's a trauma for me.</i>
<i>I almost drowned in a pool once.</i>

1790
01:29:46,600 --> 01:29:48,360
Beautiful. Good.

1791
01:29:48,440 --> 01:29:50,920
They're awkward.
Like they're trying too hard.

1792
01:29:51,000 --> 01:29:53,760
First time in my life. Going all out.

1793
01:30:00,440 --> 01:30:02,160
Subtitle translation by: Sarunpon T.
